// D&D 5e Subclass Data — auto-extracted from player.html

var IMPORTED_MISSING_SUBCLASSES={"Fighter":[{"name":"Eldritch Knight (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"The Eldritch Knight archetype combines the martial mastery common to all fighters with a careful study of magic. Eldritch Knights use magical techniques similar to those practiced by Wizards, focusing on spells of abjuration and evocation. They learn a comparatively small number of spells, committing them to memory instead of keeping a spellbook.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Spellcasting","desc":"You augment your martial prowess with the ability to cast spells. You learn three Wizard cantrips and know two 1st-level Wizard spells, both of which must be from the Abjuration or Evocation schools. You can replace one known spell each time you gain a Fighter level. INT is your spellcasting ability. You can use a weapon with which you have proficiency as a spellcasting focus."},{"level":3,"name":"War Bond","desc":"You learn a ritual that creates a magical bond between yourself and one weapon. You perform the ritual over 1 hour, touching the weapon throughout. You can call the bonded weapon to your hand as a Bonus Action if it's on the same plane of existence. You can have up to two bonded weapons, but can summon only one at a time."},{"level":7,"name":"War Magic","desc":"When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace one of the attacks with a casting of one of your Wizard cantrips that has a casting time of an action."},{"level":10,"name":"Eldritch Strike","desc":"When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, that creature has Disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes against a spell you cast before the end of your next turn."},{"level":15,"name":"Arcane Charge","desc":"When you use your Action Surge, you can teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see, either before or after the additional action."},{"level":18,"name":"Improved War Magic","desc":"When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace two of the attacks with a casting of one of your Wizard spells that has a casting time of an action."}]}],"Monk":[{"name":"Way of the Elements","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"You follow a monastic tradition that teaches you to harness the elements. When you focus your ki, you can align yourself with the forces of creation and bend the four elements to your will, using them as an extension of your body. Some adherents choose a single element, while others weave all four into their practice.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Elemental Attunement","desc":"You can spend 1 ki point as a Bonus Action to cause elemental energy to emanate from you. Choose Acid, Cold, Fire, or Lightning. Until the start of your next turn, you gain resistance to that damage type, and when you hit with an unarmed strike you can deal that damage type instead of the normal damage."},{"level":3,"name":"Elemental Burst","desc":"You can spend 2 ki points to cast one of the following spells (Spell save DC = ki save DC): Burning Hands (fire), Thunderwave (thunder), Create or Destroy Water (water), or Earthen Grasp (earth). Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for these spells."},{"level":6,"name":"Environmental Stride","desc":"You can move across water surfaces without sinking, across difficult terrain caused by ice or snow without penalty, and you can climb vertical surfaces without needing a free hand. Additionally, you take no damage from extreme heat or cold environments."},{"level":11,"name":"Elemental Epitome","desc":"When you use Elemental Attunement, you can choose two damage types instead of one. Additionally, once per turn when you deal elemental damage with your unarmed strike, you can spend 1 ki point to deal an extra 1d10 damage of that type."},{"level":17,"name":"Elemental Mastery","desc":"You can spend 4 ki points to cast one of the following spells: Fire Storm, Control Water, Wall of Fire, or Earthquake. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability. You can also spend 1 ki point as a reaction when you would take elemental damage (acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder) to gain immunity to that instance of damage."}]}],"Paladin":[{"name":"Oath of the Ancients (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"The Oath of the Ancients is as old as the race of elves and the rituals of the druids. Sometimes called fey knights, green knights, or horned knights, paladins who swear this oath cast their lot with the side of the light in the cosmic struggle against darkness because they love the beautiful and life-giving things of the world, not necessarily because they seek the destruction of the corrupt.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Oath Spells","desc":"You always have the following spells prepared: Ensnaring Strike, Speak with Animals (level 3); Misty Step, Moonbeam (level 5); Plant Growth, Protection from Energy (level 9); Ice Storm, Stoneskin (level 13); Commune with Nature, Tree Stride (level 17)."},{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Nature's Wrath","desc":"You can use your Channel Divinity to invoke primeval forces to ensnare a foe. As an action, you can cause spectral vines to spring up and reach for one creature within 10 feet of you that you can see. The creature must succeed on a Strength or Dexterity saving throw (its choice) or be Restrained. While Restrained by the vines, the creature repeats this saving throw at the end of each of its turns. On a success, it frees itself."},{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Turn the Faithless","desc":"You can use your Channel Divinity to utter ancient words that are painful for fey and fiends to hear. As an action, you present your holy symbol, and each fey or fiend within 30 feet of you that can hear you must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is turned for 1 minute or until it takes damage. A turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from you as it can."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Warding","desc":"Ancient magic lies so heavily upon you that it forms an eldritch ward. You and friendly creatures within 10 feet of you have resistance to damage from spells. At level 18, the range increases to 30 feet."},{"level":15,"name":"Undying Sentinel","desc":"When you are reduced to 0 hit points and are not killed outright, you can choose to drop to 1 hit point instead. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest. Additionally, you suffer none of the drawbacks of old age, and you can't be aged magically."},{"level":20,"name":"Elder Champion","desc":"You can assume the form of an ancient force of nature, taking on an appearance you choose (thorns, moss, antlers, etc.). For 1 minute you gain: at the start of each of your turns you regain 10 hit points; you can cast paladin spells with a casting time of 1 action as a Bonus Action; friendly creatures within 10 feet of you have advantage on saving throws against spells and magical effects. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of Vengeance (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"The Oath of Vengeance is a solemn commitment to punish those who have committed a grievous sin. When evil forces slaughter helpless villagers, when an entire people turns against the will of the gods, when a thieves' guild grows too powerful and violent, when a dragon rampages through the countryside — at times like these, paladins arise and swear an Oath of Vengeance to set right that which has gone wrong.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Oath Spells","desc":"You always have the following spells prepared: Bane, Hunter's Mark (level 3); Hold Person, Misty Step (level 5); Haste, Protection from Energy (level 9); Banishment, Dimension Door (level 13); Hold Monster, Scrying (level 17)."},{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Abjure the Extraplanar","desc":"As an action, you present your holy symbol and speak a prayer censuring fiends, undead, aberrations, elementals, and fey. Each such creature within 30 feet of you that can hear you must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is turned for 1 minute or until it takes damage."},{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Vow of Enmity","desc":"As a Bonus Action, you can utter a vow of enmity against a creature you can see within 10 feet of you, using your Channel Divinity. You gain Advantage on attack rolls against the creature for 1 minute or until it drops to 0 hit points or falls unconscious."},{"level":7,"name":"Relentless Avenger","desc":"Your supernatural focus helps you close off a foe's retreat. When you hit a creature with an opportunity attack, you can move up to half your speed immediately after the attack and as part of the same reaction. This movement doesn't provoke opportunity attacks."},{"level":15,"name":"Soul of Vengeance","desc":"The authority with which you speak your Vow of Enmity gives you greater power over your foe. When a creature under the effect of your Vow of Enmity makes an attack, you can use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against that creature if it is within range."},{"level":20,"name":"Avenging Angel","desc":"You can assume the form of an angelic avenger. For 1 hour you gain: wings with 60-foot fly speed; an aura of menace in a 30-foot radius — enemies in the aura must make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of their turn or be Frightened of you until the aura ends. A creature that saves is immune to the aura for 24 hours. Once per long rest."}]}],"Rogue":[{"name":"Arcane Trickster (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Some rogues enhance their fine-honed skills of stealth and agility with magic, learning tricks of enchantment and illusion. These arcane tricksters include pickpockets and burglars, but also pranksters and mischief-makers.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Spellcasting","desc":"You learn three Wizard cantrips (Mage Hand plus two others) and two 1st-level Wizard spells, both from the Enchantment or Illusion school. INT is your spellcasting ability. You can use a Mage Hand conjured by this class to perform the somatic components of Wizard spells, and it can be invisible."},{"level":3,"name":"Mage Hand Legerdemain","desc":"When you cast Mage Hand, the spectral hand can perform tasks that require a Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check. You can also use the hand to stow or retrieve an object from a container worn by another creature, or to use thieves' tools to pick locks and disarm traps at range. You can perform these tasks without being seen if the hand is invisible."},{"level":9,"name":"Magical Ambush","desc":"If you are hidden from a creature when you cast a spell on it, the creature has Disadvantage on any saving throw it makes against the spell this turn."},{"level":13,"name":"Versatile Trickster","desc":"You gain the ability to distract targets with your Mage Hand. As a Bonus Action on your turn, you can designate a creature within 5 feet of the spectral hand created by the spell. Doing so gives you Advantage on attack rolls against that creature until the end of the turn."},{"level":17,"name":"Spell Thief","desc":"You gain the ability to magically steal the knowledge of how to cast a spell from another spellcaster. Immediately after a creature casts a spell targeting you or including you in its area, you can use your reaction to force the caster to make a saving throw with its spellcasting ability modifier. On a failed save, you negate the spell's effect against you, and you steal the knowledge of the spell if it is at least 1st level and of a level you can cast. For the next 8 hours, you know the spell and can cast it using your spell slots. The caster can't cast the stolen spell until the 8 hours have passed. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest."}]}],"Wizard":[{"name":"Chronurgy Magic","source":"Explorer's Guide to Wildemount","desc":"Focusing on the manipulation of time, those who follow the Chronurgy tradition learn to alter the pace of reality to their liking. Using the ramping of anticipatory dunamis energy, these mages can bend the flow of time as adroitly as any skilled artisan shapes clay — or so the old saying among students of the Chronurgy tradition goes.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Chronal Shift","desc":"You can magically influence the flow of time around a creature. When a creature you can see within 30 feet of you makes an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, you can use your reaction to reroll the die. You make this decision after you see the initial roll but before the DM says whether it succeeds or fails. The creature must use the result of the second roll. You can use this feature twice per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Temporal Awareness","desc":"You can add your Intelligence modifier to your initiative rolls."},{"level":6,"name":"Momentary Stasis","desc":"As an action, you can magically force a Large or smaller creature you can see within 60 feet of you to make a Constitution saving throw against your Wizard spell save DC. On a failed save, the creature is encased in a field of magical energy until the end of your next turn or until it takes any damage. While encased, the creature has a speed of 0 and is Incapacitated. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Arcane Abeyance","desc":"When you cast a spell using a spell slot of 4th level or lower, you can condense the spell's magic into a mote. The mote is a Tiny object and lasts until you finish a long rest or until you use a Bonus Action to release the magic as the spell. A creature that picks up the mote can use a Bonus Action to trigger the spell. The spell uses your spellcasting ability and requires no verbal, somatic, or material components. Once you create a mote, you can't do so again until you finish a short or long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Convergent Future","desc":"You can peer through possible futures and magically pull one of them into reality. When you or a creature you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, you can use your reaction to ignore the die roll and decide whether the number rolled is the minimum needed to succeed or one below that minimum. When you use this feature, you gain one level of exhaustion. Only a long rest can remove this exhaustion."}]},{"name":"Graviturgy Magic","source":"Explorer's Guide to Wildemount","desc":"Understanding and mastering the forces that draw bodies of matter together or drive them apart, the graviturgy tradition is one that focuses on the most fundamental aspects of physical reality — the push and pull of the world itself. Students of the Graviturgy tradition learn spells to repel and attract, bending gravity to their will.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Adjust Density","desc":"As an action, you can magically alter the weight of one object or creature you can see within 30 feet of you. The object or creature must be Large or smaller. The target's weight is halved or doubled for up to 1 minute or until your concentration is broken (as if concentrating on a spell). Halved weight: the creature's jump distance is doubled, and it has Disadvantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. Doubled weight: the creature's speed is reduced by 10 feet, and it has Advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum once), regaining uses on a long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Gravity Well","desc":"Whenever you cast a spell on a creature, you can move the target 5 feet toward or away from you (your choice). This movement doesn't trigger opportunity attacks."},{"level":10,"name":"Violent Attraction","desc":"When another creature that you can see within 60 feet of you hits with a weapon attack, you can use your reaction to increase the attack's velocity, causing the attack's weapon to deal an extra 1d10 damage of its type. Alternatively, if a creature within 60 feet of you takes damage from a fall, you can use your reaction to increase the fall's damage by 2d10. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum once), regaining uses on a long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Event Horizon","desc":"As an action, you can magically emit a powerful field of gravitational energy that tugs at other creatures for up to 1 minute or until your concentration is broken (as if concentrating on a spell). For the duration, whenever a creature hostile to you starts its turn within 30 feet of you, it must make a Strength saving throw against your Wizard spell save DC. On a failed save, its speed is reduced to 0 until the start of its next turn. If the creature is in the air when it fails its save, it instead falls at a rate of 60 feet per round until it reaches the ground or the spell ends. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a long rest, unless you expend a spell slot of 3rd level or higher to use it again."}]}]};
var BUNDLED_FULL_SUBCLASSES={"Barbarian":[{"name":"Path of the Berserker (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Berserkers channel their rage into a violent frenzy, sacrificing their body to deal devastating damage.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Frenzy","desc":"While raging, you can go into a frenzy. You can make a single melee weapon attack as a bonus action on each of your turns. When your rage ends, you suffer one level of exhaustion."},{"level":6,"name":"Mindless Rage","desc":"You can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If you are charmed or frightened when you enter your rage, the effect is suspended for the duration of the rage."},{"level":10,"name":"Intimidating Presence","desc":"As an action, you can frighten someone with your menacing presence. One creature you can see within 30 feet makes a Wisdom saving throw (DC = 8 + proficiency + Charisma modifier) or is frightened until end of your next turn."},{"level":14,"name":"Retaliation","desc":"When you take damage from a creature within 5 feet, you can use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against that creature."}]},{"name":"Path of the Berserker (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Berserkers enter a bloodthirsty frenzy, attacking with reckless ferocity and shrugging off exhaustion through sheer will.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Frenzy","desc":"If you use Reckless Attack while your Rage is active, you deal extra damage to the first target you hit on your turn with a Strength-based attack. The extra damage equals your Rage Damage bonus. This damage is of the same type as the weapon's damage. You don't suffer exhaustion from Frenzy."},{"level":6,"name":"Mindless Rage","desc":"You can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If you are charmed or frightened when you enter Rage, that condition is suspended for the duration of the Rage."},{"level":10,"name":"Retaliation","desc":"When you take damage from a creature within 5 feet, you can use your Reaction to make one melee attack against that creature, using your Rage Damage bonus as extra damage if it hits."},{"level":14,"name":"Intimidating Presence","desc":"As a Bonus Action, you can strike terror into others. One creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC = 8 + proficiency bonus + Charisma modifier) or have the Frightened condition until the start of your next turn."}]},{"name":"Path of the Totem Warrior (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Totem Warriors form spiritual bonds with animal totems, gaining primal powers inspired by bear, eagle, wolf, and other totems.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Spirit Seeker","desc":"You can cast Beast Sense and Speak with Animals as rituals."},{"level":3,"name":"Totem Spirit","desc":"Choose Bear (resistance to all damage except psychic while raging), Eagle (Dash as bonus action; opportunity attacks against you have disadvantage while raging), Wolf (allies have advantage on melee attacks against enemies adjacent to you while raging), Elk (speed +15 ft while raging), or Tiger (you can make two extra attacks with a bonus action after taking the Dash action while raging)."},{"level":6,"name":"Aspect of the Beast","desc":"Choose Bear (carrying capacity doubles; advantage on Strength checks for pushing/pulling/lifting/grappling), Eagle (see 1 mile clearly; dim light not a penalty for Perception), Wolf (track by scent; advantage on Survival for tracking), Elk (+15 ft speed when not raging), or Tiger (proficiency in two skills from Acrobatics, Athletics, Stealth, and Survival)."},{"level":10,"name":"Spirit Walker","desc":"You can cast Commune with Nature as a ritual."},{"level":14,"name":"Totemic Attunement","desc":"Choose Bear (creatures have disadvantage on attacks against allies within 5 ft of you while raging), Eagle (fly speed = walk speed while raging; can't wear medium/heavy armor), Wolf (knocked prone creatures become targets of opportunity attacks from your allies while raging), Elk (charge 20 ft in a straight line, knock prone on failed DC 15 Strength save), or Tiger (if you move 20 ft straight toward a target you hit, knock them prone)."}]},{"name":"Path of the Wild Heart (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Replaces Totem Warrior in the 2024 PHB. Wild Heart barbarians bond with the spirits of animals, drawing on their primal power.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Animal Speaker","desc":"You can cast Beast Sense and Speak with Animals using this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Rage of the Wilds","desc":"Your Rage taps into the primal power of animals. Whenever you activate Rage, choose one: Bear (resistance to all damage except Psychic while raging), Eagle (take the Dash action as a Bonus Action; opportunity attacks against you have Disadvantage), or Wolf (your allies have Advantage on attack rolls against any enemy within 5 feet of you that isn't Incapacitated)."},{"level":6,"name":"Aspect of the Wilds","desc":"You gain a magical benefit based on the totem animal of your choice. Choose Owl (Darkvision out to 60 feet; dim light not a Disadvantage for Perception), Panther (climbing speed equal to walking speed; no difficult terrain penalty for climbing), or Salmon (swimming speed equal to walking speed; can breathe underwater). This benefit lasts until you choose a different one at the end of a Long Rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Nature Speaker","desc":"You can cast Commune with Nature using this feature. You regain the ability to do so when you finish a Long Rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Power of the Wilds","desc":"Whenever you activate Rage, choose one of the following benefits that lasts until your Rage ends: Falcon (you have a Fly Speed equal to your Speed if you aren't wearing Heavy Armor), Lion (once per turn, when you hit a creature under the effect of your Rage, you can move up to 15 feet toward them as a Bonus Action without provoking opportunity attacks), Ram (when you hit a creature with an attack, that creature must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 15 feet in a direction of your choice)."}]},{"name":"Path of the Ancestral Guardian","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Ancestral Guardians summon the spirits of their ancestors in battle, using them to protect allies and hound enemies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Ancestral Protectors","desc":"While raging, the first creature you hit with an attack becomes the target of your ancestral spirits. That creature has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you, and anyone other than you who is hit by that creature takes half the damage (reaction)."},{"level":6,"name":"Spirit Shield","desc":"While raging, if another creature you can see within 30 feet takes damage, you can use your reaction to reduce that damage by 2d6 (increases to 3d6 at level 10 and 4d6 at level 14)."},{"level":10,"name":"Consult the Spirits","desc":"You can cast Clairvoyance or Augury (without components) once per short/long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Vengeful Ancestors","desc":"When Spirit Shield reduces damage, the attacker takes force damage equal to the amount reduced."}]},{"name":"Path of the Storm Herald","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Storm Heralds are elemental warriors who emanate storm energy matching their chosen environment: desert, sea, or tundra.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Storm Aura","desc":"While raging, you emanate a 10-foot aura. Choose Desert (enemies take 2 fire damage), Sea (one creature takes 1d6 lightning damage; Dex save for half), or Tundra (allies gain 2 temporary HP). Scales by level."},{"level":6,"name":"Storm Soul","desc":"Desert: resistance to fire, unharmed by nonmagical extreme heat. Sea: resistance to lightning, can breathe underwater, swim speed 30 ft. Tundra: resistance to cold, unharmed by nonmagical extreme cold."},{"level":10,"name":"Shielding Storm","desc":"Your Storm Soul resistance extends to allies within 10 feet of you."},{"level":14,"name":"Raging Storm","desc":"Desert: when hit by a melee attack within 5 ft, the attacker makes a Dex save or takes fire damage and falls prone. Sea: when you hit with an attack, move the target up to 20 ft (thunderous push). Tundra: when you activate Storm Aura, you can freeze the ground; speed reduced for enemies in the aura."}]},{"name":"Path of the Zealot","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Zealots are so devoted to their deity that divine power courses through their rage, making them nearly impossible to kill.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Divine Fury","desc":"While raging, the first creature you hit on each turn takes extra radiant or necrotic damage (1d6 + half Barbarian level)."},{"level":3,"name":"Warrior of the Gods","desc":"Spells that would return you to life (like Revivify or Raise Dead) require no material components when cast on you."},{"level":6,"name":"Fanatical Focus","desc":"Once per rage, if you fail a saving throw, you can reroll and must use the new roll."},{"level":10,"name":"Zealous Presence","desc":"As a bonus action, unleash a battle cry. Up to 10 creatures of your choice within 60 feet gain advantage on attack rolls and saving throws until the start of your next turn. Once per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Rage Beyond Death","desc":"While raging, having 0 HP doesn't knock you unconscious. You still make death saving throws and die on 3 failures, but you can continue fighting until your rage ends."}]},{"name":"Path of Wild Magic","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Wild Magic Barbarians channel chaotic magical energy through their rage, producing unpredictable and powerful effects.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Magic Awareness","desc":"As an action, you can sense magic. Until end of next turn, you know if any spell or magic item is within 60 feet and the school of any spells you detect. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Wild Surge","desc":"When you enter rage, roll on the Wild Magic table. Effects include: aura of magic bolts, summoning a spirit, teleportation, speeding up allies, damaging aura, growth, and more."},{"level":6,"name":"Bolstering Magic","desc":"As an action, touch a creature (including yourself). Roll d3: 1) +1d3 bonus to all attack rolls and ability checks for 10 minutes. 2) Regain one expended spell slot of level 1d3."},{"level":10,"name":"Unstable Backlash","desc":"When you take damage or fail a saving throw while raging, use your reaction to roll on Wild Surge again, replacing the current effect."},{"level":14,"name":"Controlled Surge","desc":"When you roll on Wild Surge, roll twice and choose which result to use."}]},{"name":"Path of the Beast","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Beast Barbarians tap into a primal beastial nature, transforming parts of their body into natural weapons.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Form of the Beast","desc":"While raging, your body becomes a natural weapon. Choose each rage: Bite (1d8 piercing; heal HP equal to prof bonus once per turn), Claws (extra attack with claws as bonus action), or Tail (1d8 piercing reach weapon; reaction to add +1d8 to AC against one hit per turn)."},{"level":6,"name":"Bestial Soul","desc":"Unarmed strikes count as magical. At end of a short/long rest, choose a permanent benefit: swim speed = walk speed, climb speed = walk speed, or jump distance doubles."},{"level":10,"name":"Infectious Fury","desc":"When you hit with natural weapons while raging, you can force the target to make a Wisdom save (DC = 8 + prof + Con modifier) or suffer one of: target must use reaction to attack another creature of your choice, or target takes 2d12 psychic damage. Prof bonus times per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Call the Hunt","desc":"When you enter a rage, up to 5 willing creatures you can see within 30 feet gain the benefit of one of your Form of the Beast natural weapons for the duration. They deal 1d6 extra damage on hits. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Path of the World Tree","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"New in 2024 PHB. World Tree Barbarians draw power from Yggdrasil, channeling its cosmic energy to protect allies and traverse the planes.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Vitality Surge","desc":"When you activate Rage, you gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Barbarian level. Additionally, choose a willing creature you can see within 30 feet; they also gain the same Temporary Hit Points."},{"level":6,"name":"Branches of the Tree","desc":"While raging, you can use your Reaction to teleport a creature that hits you or a creature you can see within 30 feet to an unoccupied space within 5 feet of you (with their consent) or up to 30 feet away (Strength saving throw to resist; on failure they also have Speed 0 until end of their next turn)."},{"level":10,"name":"Battering Roots","desc":"Your reach increases by 10 feet for melee attacks you make with Heavy or Versatile weapons while raging."},{"level":14,"name":"Travel Along the Tree","desc":"When you activate Rage, and as a Bonus Action on subsequent turns of your Rage, you can teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space. On reaching level 20, you can instead teleport to a different plane of existence."}]},{"name":"Path of the Giant","source":"Bigby Presents: Glory of the Giants","desc":"Giant Barbarians channel the power of primordial giants, growing in size and power as their rage builds.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Giant's Power","desc":"You learn Giant or one other language. You learn the Elemental Burst cantrip (choose acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder). Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Giant's Havoc","desc":"While raging: your reach increases by 5 feet, you can add your Rage Damage bonus to thrown weapon attacks, and once per turn, when you hit a creature with an attack, you can deal extra damage equal to your proficiency bonus to another creature within 10 feet of the first."},{"level":6,"name":"Elemental Cleaver","desc":"While raging, one weapon you hold deals extra elemental damage (equal to Rage Damage bonus) of the type you chose in Giant's Power."},{"level":10,"name":"Mighty Impel","desc":"As a bonus action while raging, you can pull a creature within reach to an unoccupied space within 5 feet, or throw it up to 30 feet. Strength saving throw resists. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Demiurgic Colossus","desc":"While raging, your size becomes Large (or Huge if your campaign allows) if you were Medium or smaller. Your reach increases by 10 feet instead of 5. You gain resistance to the damage type of your Elemental Cleaver."}]}],"Bard":[{"name":"College of Lore (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Lore Bards collect knowledge from every corner of the world, honing their skills and magic.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"You gain proficiency in three skills of your choice."},{"level":3,"name":"Cutting Words","desc":"When a creature you can see within 60 feet makes an attack roll, ability check, or damage roll, you can use your reaction and expend one Bardic Inspiration die to subtract the roll from the creature's result."},{"level":6,"name":"Additional Magical Secrets","desc":"Choose two spells from any class. They count as bard spells and don't count against your spells known."},{"level":14,"name":"Peerless Skill","desc":"When you make an ability check, you can expend one Bardic Inspiration die and add the roll to your check. Usable before or after the roll."}]},{"name":"College of Lore (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in the 2024 PHB with revised Cutting Words and new Peerless Skill mechanics.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"You gain proficiency in three skills of your choice."},{"level":3,"name":"Cutting Words","desc":"Whenever a creature that you can see within 60 feet succeeds on an ability check or attack roll, you can use your Reaction to expend one use of your Bardic Inspiration and reduce the creature's roll by the number rolled on the Bardic Inspiration die, potentially turning success into failure."},{"level":6,"name":"Magical Discoveries","desc":"Choose two spells from any class list; they are always prepared for you and count as Bard spells."},{"level":14,"name":"Peerless Skill","desc":"When you make a Strength, Dexterity, Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma check and roll a 9 or lower on the d20, you can use Bardic Inspiration as if you'd used Cutting Words (but subtracting from your own roll's failure margin, effectively treating it as a higher result)."}]},{"name":"College of Valor (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Valor Bards inspire greatness on the battlefield, blending swordplay and spellcasting.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"You gain proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons."},{"level":3,"name":"Combat Inspiration","desc":"A creature that has a Bardic Inspiration die can roll it and add the result to a weapon damage roll or to its AC against one attack (reaction when hit)."},{"level":6,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"You can attack twice instead of once when you take the Attack action."},{"level":14,"name":"Battle Magic","desc":"When you use your action to cast a Bard spell, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action."}]},{"name":"College of Valor (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in 2024 PHB with the Combat Inspiration die now also applying to saving throws.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Martial Training","desc":"You gain proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons."},{"level":3,"name":"Combat Inspiration","desc":"A creature with a Bardic Inspiration die can use it to add the result to a weapon damage roll, to their AC against one attack (reaction), or to a saving throw (reaction)."},{"level":6,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"You can attack twice instead of once when you take the Attack action on your turn."},{"level":14,"name":"Battle Magic","desc":"When you cast a Bard spell using your action, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action."}]},{"name":"College of Glamour","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Glamour Bards wield the captivating magic of the Feywild, enthralling enemies and inspiring awe in allies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Mantle of Inspiration","desc":"As a bonus action, expend one Bardic Inspiration to give up to five creatures you can see within 60 feet temporary HP equal to your Charisma modifier + Bardic Inspiration die roll, and they can each use their reaction to move up to their speed without provoking opportunity attacks."},{"level":3,"name":"Enthralling Performance","desc":"Over 1 minute of performance, charm up to 5 creatures within 60 feet (Wisdom save DC = 8 + prof + Cha modifier). Charmed for 1 hour; they become friendly and can be asked for favors. Once per short or long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Mantle of Majesty","desc":"As a bonus action, you appear supernaturally beautiful and cast Command (no spell slot) each turn for 1 minute. Creatures charmed by Enthralling Performance auto-fail the save. Once per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Unbreakable Majesty","desc":"As a bonus action, gain an unearthly appearance for 1 minute. Whenever a creature attacks you, it must make a Charisma save (DC = 8 + prof + Cha) or choose a different target. If it passes, the effect ends. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"College of Swords","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Swords Bards master blade-spinning and combat performance, combining martial prowess with Bardic flair.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"You gain proficiency with medium armor and the scimitar. If you are proficient with a simple or martial melee weapon, you can use it as a spellcasting focus."},{"level":3,"name":"Fighting Style","desc":"You adopt a Fighting Style from the Fighter list: Dueling or Two-Weapon Fighting."},{"level":3,"name":"Blade Flourish","desc":"Once per turn when you make a weapon attack, you can expend one Bardic Inspiration die and use a Blade Flourish: Defensive Flourish (add die to AC and damage), Slashing Flourish (add die to damage to another creature within 5 ft), or Mobile Flourish (push target up to 5 + die result ft; move to space adjacent to target without provoking)."},{"level":6,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"You can attack twice instead of once when you take the Attack action."},{"level":14,"name":"Master's Flourish","desc":"When you use a Blade Flourish, you can roll a d6 and use it instead of expending a Bardic Inspiration die."}]},{"name":"College of Whispers","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Whispers Bards are masters of secrets and manipulation, blending in among any group while gathering information.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Psychic Blades","desc":"When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, expend one Bardic Inspiration die to deal extra psychic damage (2d6 at 5th, 3d6 at 10th, 5d6 at 15th)."},{"level":3,"name":"Words of Terror","desc":"Over 1 minute of whispered speaking with a humanoid alone, frighten them for 1 hour (Wisdom save, DC = 8 + prof + Cha modifier). Once per short or long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Mantle of Whispers","desc":"When a humanoid dies within 30 feet, you can capture their shadow (reaction). As an action, disguise yourself as them (using their memories and appearance) for 1 hour or until you drop to 0 HP. Once per short or long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Shadow Lore","desc":"As an action, whisper to a creature within 30 feet. It must make a Wisdom save (DC = 8 + prof + Cha modifier) or be charmed for 8 hours. While charmed, it believes you know its most humiliating secret and will do anything to prevent you sharing it. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"College of Eloquence","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Mythic Odysseys of Theros","desc":"Eloquence Bards are supreme orators whose Bardic Inspiration is so potent it never goes to waste.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Silver Tongue","desc":"When you make a Persuasion or Deception check, treat a roll of 9 or lower on the d20 as a 10."},{"level":3,"name":"Unsettling Words","desc":"As a bonus action, expend one Bardic Inspiration die and choose a creature within 60 feet. Roll the die; the creature subtracts that amount from the next saving throw it makes before the start of your next turn."},{"level":6,"name":"Unfailing Inspiration","desc":"When a creature adds your Bardic Inspiration die to a roll and fails, they keep the die; they don't expend it."},{"level":6,"name":"Universal Speech","desc":"As an action, any number of creatures within 60 feet understand your words (any language) for 1 hour. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Infectious Inspiration","desc":"When a creature uses your Bardic Inspiration successfully, you can use your reaction to give another creature within 60 feet a Bardic Inspiration die for free (no expending your own)."}]},{"name":"College of Creation","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Creation Bards tap into the primordial Song of Creation, animating objects and weaving magic into reality.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Mote of Potential","desc":"When a creature has your Bardic Inspiration die, it gains extra benefits: ability check (roll the die twice, take higher), attack roll (pull a mote of potential to give all creatures within 5 ft of target thunder damage equal to the die), or saving throw (the creature and allies within 5 ft gain temp HP equal to the die + Charisma modifier)."},{"level":3,"name":"Performance of Creation","desc":"As an action, create one nonmagical item of up to 20 gp value in an unoccupied space within 10 feet. It lasts for hours equal to Charisma modifier (minimum 1). Once per long rest (or burn a spell slot of 2nd level or higher to do it again). Item size limited by Bard level."},{"level":6,"name":"Animating Performance","desc":"As an action, target one Large or smaller nonmagical item within 30 feet. It becomes a Dancing Item under your control (uses your bonus action to command). Once per long rest (or burn a 3rd-level spell slot)."},{"level":14,"name":"Creative Crescendo","desc":"When you use Performance of Creation, you create up to Charisma modifier items at once (minimum 1). Items of up to Huge size can be created."}]},{"name":"College of Dance","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"New in 2024 PHB. Dance Bards use graceful movement as their art form, combining acrobatics with devastating footwork.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Dazzling Footwork","desc":"While not wearing armor or carrying a shield, you gain Unarmored Defense (AC = 10 + Dex modifier + Charisma modifier). Additionally, when you successfully Bardic Inspire a creature, you can deal 1d6 + Charisma modifier Bludgeoning damage to one creature within 5 feet (Agile Strikes)."},{"level":6,"name":"Inspiring Movement","desc":"When an enemy ends its turn within 5 feet of you, you can use your Reaction to move up to half your speed without provoking opportunity attacks, and grant one ally within 30 feet who can see you the ability to also move up to half their speed without provoking opportunity attacks."},{"level":14,"name":"Leading Evasion","desc":"When you use Evasion (from the Bard's 14th-level feature), you can extend Evasion to any creature within 5 feet of you who is also subjected to the effect."}]}],"Cleric":[{"name":"Life Domain (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Life Clerics channel powerful healing magic, keeping allies standing through even the most devastating battles.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiency","desc":"You gain proficiency with heavy armor."},{"level":1,"name":"Disciple of Life","desc":"Whenever you use a spell of 1st level or higher to restore hit points, the creature regains additional HP equal to 2 + the spell's level."},{"level":2,"name":"Preserve Life","desc":"Channel Divinity: restore HP to creatures within 30 feet, distributing up to 5× your Cleric level in HP. Can't restore above half max HP."},{"level":6,"name":"Blessed Healer","desc":"When you cast a healing spell on a creature other than yourself, you also regain HP equal to 2 + the spell's level."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, your weapon attacks deal extra radiant damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th level."},{"level":17,"name":"Supreme Healing","desc":"When you would roll dice to restore HP, instead use the maximum number for each die."}]},{"name":"Life Domain (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in 2024 PHB. Life Domain now uses Potent Spellcasting instead of Divine Strike.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Life Domain Spells","desc":"Aid, Bless, Cure Wounds, Lesser Restoration, Mass Cure Wounds, Revivify are always prepared."},{"level":3,"name":"Disciple of Life","desc":"Whenever a spell you cast restores Hit Points to a creature, that creature regains additional Hit Points equal to 2 + the spell's level."},{"level":3,"name":"Preserve Life","desc":"Channel Divinity: as a Magic action, restore HP to creatures within 30 feet (total = 5× Cleric level). Can't bring above half max HP."},{"level":6,"name":"Blessed Healer","desc":"When you cast a spell that restores HP to a creature other than yourself, you regain HP equal to 2 + the spell's level."},{"level":11,"name":"Supreme Healing","desc":"When you would roll dice for a healing spell, use the maximum number for each die."},{"level":17,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"You add your Wisdom modifier to the damage you deal with any Cleric cantrip."}]},{"name":"Light Domain (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Light Clerics wield fire and radiance, blasting enemies with divine brilliance.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Cantrip","desc":"You gain the Light cantrip."},{"level":1,"name":"Warding Flare","desc":"When a creature attacks you, you can interpose divine light as a reaction: the attacker has disadvantage on its attack roll. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Radiance of the Dawn","desc":"Channel Divinity: dispel magical darkness in 30 feet; hostile creatures within 30 feet take 2d10 + Cleric level radiant damage (Con save for half)."},{"level":6,"name":"Improved Flare","desc":"When a creature attacks a creature other than you (that you can see within 30 feet), you can use Warding Flare."},{"level":8,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"You add your Wisdom modifier to the damage you deal with any Cleric cantrip."},{"level":17,"name":"Corona of Light","desc":"As an action, emanate a 60-foot aura of sunlight for 1 minute. Enemies in the aura have disadvantage on saving throws vs. fire or radiant spells."}]},{"name":"Light Domain (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in 2024. Warding Flare now protects allies by default; Radiance of the Dawn expanded.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Light Domain Spells","desc":"Burning Hands, Faerie Fire, Fireball, Guiding Bolt, Moonbeam, Scorching Ray, Daylight, Wall of Fire are always prepared."},{"level":3,"name":"Radiance of the Dawn","desc":"Channel Divinity: dispel magical darkness within 30 feet; hostile creatures in 30 feet take 2d10 + Cleric level radiant damage (Con save for half)."},{"level":3,"name":"Warding Flare","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet is attacked (including you), you can use your Reaction to impose Disadvantage on the attack. Wisdom modifier times per Long Rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Improved Flare","desc":"You can use Warding Flare on any creature, not just yourself."},{"level":11,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"Add your Wisdom modifier to the damage of Cleric cantrips."},{"level":17,"name":"Corona of Light","desc":"As a Magic action, emanate sunlight aura for 1 minute. Hostile creatures in the aura have Disadvantage on saving throws against fire and radiant spells."}]},{"name":"Trickery Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Trickery Clerics serve gods of cunning and deception, using illusions and misdirection to outwit foes.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Blessing of the Trickster","desc":"You can use your action to grant another creature advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks for 1 hour. Once per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Invoke Duplicity","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, create an illusory duplicate of yourself within 30 feet for 1 minute. You can cast spells as though from its space. Creatures distracted by it grant you advantage on attacks."},{"level":6,"name":"Cloak of Shadows","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, become invisible until end of next turn or until you attack or cast a spell."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra poison damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th level."},{"level":17,"name":"Improved Duplicity","desc":"You can create up to four duplicates of yourself. You can move each as a bonus action and cast spells from any of their positions."}]},{"name":"War Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"War Clerics inspire martial prowess and divine strikes on the battlefield.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"You gain proficiency with heavy armor and martial weapons."},{"level":1,"name":"War Priest","desc":"When you use the Attack action, you can make a weapon attack as a bonus action. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Guided Strike","desc":"Channel Divinity: when you make an attack roll, gain +10 to the roll. Can be used after seeing the roll but before knowing the outcome."},{"level":6,"name":"War God's Blessing","desc":"Channel Divinity: when a creature within 30 feet makes an attack roll, use your reaction to grant +10 to the roll."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra damage (same type as weapon): 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Avatar of Battle","desc":"You gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical weapons."}]},{"name":"Knowledge Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Knowledge Clerics treasure learning and lore, empowering themselves and allies with forbidden secrets.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Blessings of Knowledge","desc":"Learn two languages and gain proficiency in two skills from Arcana, History, Nature, and Religion. Your proficiency bonus doubles for those skills."},{"level":2,"name":"Knowledge of the Ages","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, choose a skill or tool proficiency. For 10 minutes, you gain proficiency in that skill or tool."},{"level":2,"name":"Read Thoughts","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, read the surface thoughts of one creature within 60 feet (Wisdom save to resist). If they fail, read thoughts for 1 minute. Can then cast Suggestion on them at no spell slot."},{"level":6,"name":"Channel Divinity: Mind Control","desc":"Equivalent to Read Thoughts at this level expanded to dominate actions (see individual edition for precise rules)."},{"level":8,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"Add your Wisdom modifier to Cleric cantrip damage."},{"level":17,"name":"Visions of the Past","desc":"As an action, spend 1 minute in meditation to receive visions about a place or object (similar to Legend Lore or Object Reading)."}]},{"name":"Nature Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Nature Clerics are intermediaries between civilization and the natural world, wielding primal elemental power.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Acolyte of Nature","desc":"Learn one Druid cantrip. Gain proficiency in one of Animal Handling, Nature, or Survival."},{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiency","desc":"Proficiency with heavy armor."},{"level":2,"name":"Charm Animals and Plants","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, charm beasts and plant creatures within 30 feet. They are charmed for 1 minute or until damaged."},{"level":6,"name":"Dampen Elements","desc":"When you or a creature within 30 feet takes acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder damage, use your reaction to grant resistance against that damage."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra cold, fire, or lightning damage (choose): 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Master of Nature","desc":"You can command animals and plants charmed by your Channel Divinity as a bonus action."}]},{"name":"Tempest Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Tempest Clerics harness the fury of storms, calling down lightning and thunder on their foes.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with heavy armor and martial weapons."},{"level":1,"name":"Wrath of the Storm","desc":"When a creature within 5 feet hits you with an attack, use your reaction to deal 2d8 lightning or thunder damage (Dex save for half). Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Destructive Wrath","desc":"Channel Divinity: when you roll lightning or thunder damage, deal maximum damage instead of rolling."},{"level":6,"name":"Thunderbolt Strike","desc":"When you deal lightning damage to a Large or smaller creature, push it up to 10 feet away."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra thunder damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Stormborn","desc":"When you are not underground or indoors, you gain a fly speed equal to your current walk speed."}]},{"name":"Death Domain","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 (Dungeon Master option) / 2024","desc":"Death Clerics command the power of death and undeath, often serving villainous ends. Typically reserved for NPCs or dark campaigns.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiency","desc":"Proficiency with martial weapons."},{"level":1,"name":"Reaper","desc":"Learn one necromancy cantrip. Necromancy cantrips that target only one creature can now target two creatures in range."},{"level":2,"name":"Touch of Death","desc":"Channel Divinity: when you hit with a melee attack, deal extra necrotic damage equal to 5 + Cleric level × 2."},{"level":6,"name":"Inescapable Destruction","desc":"Necrotic damage you deal ignores resistance."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra necrotic damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Improved Reaper","desc":"Spells of 1st through 5th level that target only one creature can target two creatures in range (no double components needed)."}]},{"name":"Forge Domain","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Forge Clerics serve gods of craft and creation, blessing weapons and armor and shaping metal with divine power.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with heavy armor and Smith's tools."},{"level":1,"name":"Blessing of the Forge","desc":"At end of a long rest, touch one nonmagical weapon or armor. Until the end of your next long rest, it becomes magical with +1 to attack and damage (weapon) or +1 to AC (armor). Only one active at a time."},{"level":2,"name":"Artisan's Blessing","desc":"Channel Divinity: over a short rest, craft a nonmagical metal item worth up to 100 gp using raw materials worth at least half the cost."},{"level":6,"name":"Soul of the Forge","desc":"Resistance to fire damage. While in heavy armor, +1 AC."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra fire damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Saint of Forge and Fire","desc":"Immunity to fire damage. While wearing heavy armor, resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical weapons."}]},{"name":"Grave Domain","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Grave Clerics walk the line between life and death, ensuring the living stay living and the dead stay dead.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Circle of Mortality","desc":"Healing spells restore maximum HP when targeting a creature with 0 HP. Learn Spare the Dying (range 30 ft)."},{"level":1,"name":"Eyes of the Grave","desc":"As an action, detect undead within 60 feet (including through walls). Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Path to the Grave","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, curse a creature. The next time it takes damage, it's vulnerable to that damage. Curse ends after 1 hit."},{"level":6,"name":"Sentinel at Death's Door","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet suffers a critical hit, use your reaction to turn it into a normal hit. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":8,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"Add Wisdom modifier to Cleric cantrip damage."},{"level":17,"name":"Keeper of Souls","desc":"When a creature dies within 60 feet, you or another creature of your choice within 60 feet regains HP equal to the creature's number of Hit Dice. Once per round."}]},{"name":"Order Domain","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Guildmasters' Guide to Ravnica","desc":"Order Clerics impose divine law, commanding allies and compelling compliance from foes.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with heavy armor and the Persuasion skill."},{"level":1,"name":"Voice of Authority","desc":"When you cast a spell using a spell slot that targets at least one ally, that ally can immediately use its reaction to make one weapon attack against a creature of your choice that you can see."},{"level":2,"name":"Order's Demand","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, each creature of your choice within 30 feet must succeed on a Wisdom save or be charmed until end of next turn and drop what they're holding."},{"level":6,"name":"Embodiment of the Law","desc":"When you cast an enchantment spell of 1st level or higher, you can change its casting time to a bonus action once per turn."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra psychic damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Order's Wrath","desc":"When you hit with Divine Strike, the target is cursed until start of your next turn. The next ally to hit the cursed target deals extra 2d8 psychic damage."}]},{"name":"Peace Domain","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Peace Clerics foster harmony between creatures, binding allies together and defusing conflict.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Implement of Peace","desc":"Proficiency in Insight, Performance, or Persuasion (choose one)."},{"level":1,"name":"Emboldening Bond","desc":"As an action, create a bond among up to Proficiency Bonus creatures within 30 feet for 10 minutes. Bonded creatures add 1d4 to attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws when within 30 feet of another bonded creature. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Balm of Peace","desc":"Channel Divinity: move up to your speed without provoking opportunity attacks; restore HP equal to 2d6 + Wisdom modifier to each creature you come within 5 feet of."},{"level":6,"name":"Protective Bond","desc":"When a bonded creature is about to take damage, another bonded creature within 60 feet can use its reaction to teleport adjacent and take the damage instead."},{"level":8,"name":"Potent Spellcasting","desc":"Add Wisdom modifier to Cleric cantrip damage."},{"level":17,"name":"Expansive Bond","desc":"Protective Bond works at any range (no 60 ft limit). Bonded creatures also gain resistance to damage when using Protective Bond."}]},{"name":"Twilight Domain","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Twilight Clerics guard against the terrors of night, offering protection and comfort in darkness.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with martial weapons and heavy armor."},{"level":1,"name":"Eyes of Night","desc":"Darkvision out to 300 feet. As an action, extend this Darkvision to willing creatures within 10 feet of you for 1 hour (Wisdom modifier in creatures). Once per long rest (or by spell slot)."},{"level":1,"name":"Vigilant Blessing","desc":"Touch one creature at end of long rest; it gains advantage on initiative rolls until next long rest. Can be yourself."},{"level":2,"name":"Twilight Sanctuary","desc":"Channel Divinity: 30-foot aura of dim light for 1 minute. At end of each of your turns, you and all creatures in the aura can gain: temp HP = 1d6 + Cleric level, OR end the Frightened or Charmed condition."},{"level":6,"name":"Steps of Night","desc":"When you're in darkness or dim light, take a bonus action to fly up to 60 feet (no provoked opportunity attacks). Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":8,"name":"Divine Strike","desc":"Once per turn, weapon attacks deal extra psychic damage: 1d8 at 8th, 2d8 at 14th."},{"level":17,"name":"Twilight Shroud","desc":"You and allies within your Twilight Sanctuary gain half cover."}]}],"Druid":[{"name":"Circle of the Land (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Land Druids draw power from the natural environment of their homeland, gaining access to additional spells based on their terrain.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Bonus Cantrip","desc":"You learn one additional druid cantrip of your choice."},{"level":2,"name":"Natural Recovery","desc":"After a short rest, recover expended spell slots totaling up to half your Druid level (rounded up). Slots of 6th or higher can't be recovered. Once per long rest."},{"level":2,"name":"Circle Spells","desc":"You gain circle spells based on terrain (Arctic, Coast, Desert, Forest, Grassland, Mountain, Swamp, or Underdark). These are always prepared."},{"level":6,"name":"Land's Stride","desc":"Moving through nonmagical difficult terrain costs no extra movement. Immune to nonmagical plants that impede movement. Advantage on saves against magically created plants."},{"level":10,"name":"Nature's Ward","desc":"Can't be charmed or frightened by elementals or fey. Immune to poison and disease."},{"level":14,"name":"Nature's Sanctuary","desc":"When a beast or plant attacks you, it must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, it must choose a different target or waste the attack."}]},{"name":"Circle of the Land (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in 2024 PHB. Land's Aid replaces Bonus Cantrip; Natural Recovery now also works as a ritual-like Druid ability.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Circle Spells","desc":"Based on chosen land (Arid, Polar, Temperate, or Tropical), gain a list of always-prepared spells."},{"level":3,"name":"Land's Aid","desc":"As a Bonus Action, spend a use of Wild Shape to heal allies and damage foes: choose up to Wisdom modifier creatures within 10 feet to gain Temporary HP equal to 1d6 + Wisdom modifier; hostile creatures within 10 feet take 1d6 Necrotic damage (Con save for half)."},{"level":6,"name":"Natural Recovery","desc":"You can cast a spell without expending a spell slot once per Long Rest. The slot level can't exceed your Proficiency Bonus."},{"level":10,"name":"Nature's Ward","desc":"You can't be Charmed or Frightened by Elementals or Fey. Immune to Poison condition and Poisoned condition."},{"level":14,"name":"Nature's Sanctuary","desc":"When a Beast or Plant attacks you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or waste its attack."}]},{"name":"Circle of the Moon (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Moon Druids are powerful shapeshifters who assume the forms of fearsome beasts.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Combat Wild Shape","desc":"Use Wild Shape as a bonus action. While in Wild Shape, spend a spell slot as a bonus action to regain 1d8 HP per level of the slot."},{"level":2,"name":"Circle Forms","desc":"Can Wild Shape into beasts with CR up to 1 (level 2), CR equal to Druid level ÷ 3 (levels 2–8), and up to CR 6 with swim speed (level 6) or fly speed (level 8)."},{"level":6,"name":"Primal Strike","desc":"Your Wild Shape attacks count as magical for overcoming resistance and immunity."},{"level":10,"name":"Elemental Wild Shape","desc":"Spend two Wild Shape uses to transform into an Air, Earth, Fire, or Water Elemental."},{"level":14,"name":"Thousand Forms","desc":"You can cast Alter Self at will."}]},{"name":"Circle of the Moon (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated in 2024 PHB. Wild Shape now scales by Druid level; Moon forms gain temporary HP and magical strikes from the start.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Circle Forms","desc":"While in Wild Shape, your beast form's maximum CR equals your Druid level ÷ 3 (rounded down, minimum CR 1). Your attacks in Wild Shape count as magical."},{"level":3,"name":"Lunar Form","desc":"When you Wild Shape, you gain Temporary Hit Points equal to three times your Druid level."},{"level":6,"name":"Improved Circle Forms","desc":"While in beast form, you can use a bonus action to make your attacks deal Radiant damage, and you add your Proficiency Bonus to Concentration saving throws."},{"level":10,"name":"Elemental Wild Shape","desc":"Expend two uses of Wild Shape to transform into an Air, Earth, Fire, or Water Elemental."},{"level":14,"name":"Thousand Forms","desc":"You can cast Alter Self at will, without expending a spell slot."}]},{"name":"Circle of Dreams","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Dreams Druids are connected to the Feywild, using healing magic and teleportation to protect allies.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Balm of the Summer Court","desc":"At level 2, gain a pool of d6s equal to twice your Druid level. As a bonus action, touch a creature and expend d6s (up to Wisdom modifier) to restore that many d6 HP. If any HP is restored, the creature gains temp HP equal to remaining d6s spent."},{"level":6,"name":"Hearth of Moonlight and Shadow","desc":"During short or long rest, create a hidden camp. Creatures in the 30-foot radius gain +5 Stealth and Perception; flames in the area are invisible to outside creatures."},{"level":10,"name":"Hidden Paths","desc":"As a bonus action, teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. OR use action to teleport a willing creature within 5 feet to unoccupied space within 30 feet that the creature can see. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Walker in Dreams","desc":"After a short rest, cast one of Dream, Scrying, or Teleportation Circle (no components). The targets of these spells must be connected to your last long rest location. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Circle of the Shepherd","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Shepherd Druids speak the language of beasts and spirits, summoning powerful allies to aid in battle.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Speech of the Woods","desc":"Speak with Animals (always prepared, ritual). Learn Sylvan. All beasts can understand your speech."},{"level":2,"name":"Spirit Totem","desc":"As a bonus action, summon a spirit totem that lasts for 1 minute (once per short/long rest). Bear Spirit (temp HP = 5 + Druid level; Concentration not broken from non-incapacitating damage). Hawk Spirit (one creature per turn can use reaction to attack on your Hawk's turn, giving attacker advantage). Unicorn Spirit (healing spells also heal 1d8 to one nearby creature)."},{"level":6,"name":"Mighty Summoner","desc":"Beasts and fey you summon via spells have +2 HP per Hit Die and their attacks are magical."},{"level":10,"name":"Guardian Spirit","desc":"Beasts and fey you summon within your Spirit Totem aura regain 2d6 HP at end of each of your turns."},{"level":14,"name":"Faithful Summons","desc":"When you are incapacitated or die, four beasts (CR 2 or lower) appear within 20 feet and are under your control for 1 hour. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Circle of Spores","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Guildmasters' Guide to Ravnica","desc":"Spores Druids celebrate the cycle of life and death, wielding necromantic power through fungal spores.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Halo of Spores","desc":"When a creature moves within 10 feet of you, use your reaction to deal 1d4 necrotic damage (Con save to avoid). Damage scales at higher levels."},{"level":2,"name":"Symbiotic Entity","desc":"Use Wild Shape to grant yourself temp HP (4× Druid level) and enhance Halo of Spores. Melee attacks deal 1d6 extra necrotic. Lasts until you lose all temp HP or short/long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Fungal Infestation","desc":"When a Small or Medium beast or humanoid dies within 10 feet, use your reaction to animate it as a zombie for 1 hour (you control it). Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Spreading Spores","desc":"While Symbiotic Entity is active, use bonus action to move Halo of Spores to a 10-foot cube within 30 feet (reaction not needed; hits all who enter)."},{"level":14,"name":"Fungal Body","desc":"Immune to Blinded, Deafened, Frightened, and Poisoned. Critical hits become normal hits against you."}]},{"name":"Circle of Stars","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Stars Druids commune with the constellations, channeling their power for healing, offense, and cosmic insight.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Star Map","desc":"Create a star chart (takes 8 hours). With it: Guiding Bolt is always prepared. Guidance and Guiding Bolt count as Druid spells. Cast Guiding Bolt without a spell slot (Wisdom modifier times per long rest)."},{"level":2,"name":"Starry Form","desc":"Wild Shape transforms you into a starry form (no beast). Choose Archer (Bonus action: ranged spell attack for 1d8+Wis radiant), Chalice (when you cast a healing spell, you or another creature within 30 ft regains 1d8+Wis HP), or Dragon (Concentration checks are Advantage; minimum of 10 on die)."},{"level":6,"name":"Cosmic Omen","desc":"Roll d6 after long rest. Weal (even): reaction to add 1d6 to an attack/check/save of a visible creature. Woe (odd): reaction to subtract 1d6 from an attack/check/save of a visible creature. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Twinkling Constellations","desc":"In Starry Form, add Archer and Chalice at same time if you chose Dragon. Fly speed 20 ft if in Starry Form. Can change constellation chosen at start of each turn."},{"level":14,"name":"Full of Stars","desc":"While in Starry Form, become partially incorporeal; resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage."}]},{"name":"Circle of Wildfire","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Wildfire Druids understand the need for destruction in the cycle of nature, bonding with a wildfire spirit.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Summon Wildfire Spirit","desc":"Use Wild Shape to summon a wildfire spirit (CR —) instead of transforming. The spirit acts on your initiative; you can command it as a bonus action. It deals fire damage and can teleport allies."},{"level":2,"name":"Enhanced Bond","desc":"While your wildfire spirit is present, your spells deal +1d8 fire damage (damage spells) or restore +1d8 HP (healing spells) once per casting."},{"level":6,"name":"Cauterizing Flames","desc":"When a creature in your wildfire spirit's 10-foot range drops to 0 HP, a ghost flame appears. You or another creature can use a reaction to extinguish it and restore 2d10+Wis HP to a nearby creature. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Blazing Revival","desc":"If your wildfire spirit is within 120 feet when you drop to 0 HP, the spirit rushes to you. You drop to 1 HP instead. Your spirit is extinguished. Once per long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Firestorm","desc":"While your wildfire spirit is active, you cast Flame Strike (free), which also causes creatures within 10 feet of the spirit to automatically take fire damage. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Circle of the Sea","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"New in 2024 PHB. Sea Druids draw power from the ocean, wielding cold and lightning and reshaping the battlefield with watery magic.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Wrath of the Sea","desc":"As a Bonus Action, summon a wave of aquatic power around you. For 1 minute, once per turn when you hit a creature within 5 feet with an attack, the creature takes additional Cold damage (1d6 + Wisdom modifier) and must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 15 feet away from you and knocked Prone. Wisdom modifier times per Long Rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Ocean's Gift","desc":"You gain a Swim Speed equal to your Speed, and can breathe underwater. Always prepared: Create or Destroy Water, Thunderwave, Shatter, Water Walk, Control Water, Watery Sphere."},{"level":6,"name":"Aquatic Affinity","desc":"When you Wild Shape into a beast, you can choose to gain a Swim Speed of 60 feet and the ability to breathe underwater instead of its listed speed."},{"level":10,"name":"Stormborn","desc":"Gain a Fly Speed equal to your Speed when outdoors. Lightning spells you cast deal extra damage equal to your Proficiency Bonus."},{"level":14,"name":"Oceanic Gift","desc":"When you cast Wrath of the Sea, you can extend its effects to up to 5 other willing creatures within 30 feet. Each creature gains all the benefits for the duration."}]}],"Fighter":[{"name":"Champion (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Champions focus on the development of raw physical power, pushing their martial skills to peak levels.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Improved Critical","desc":"Your weapon attacks score a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20."},{"level":7,"name":"Remarkable Athlete","desc":"Add half your proficiency bonus (rounded up) to Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution checks that don't use your proficiency bonus. Running long jump distance increases by Strength modifier feet."},{"level":10,"name":"Additional Fighting Style","desc":"Choose a second option from the Fighting Style class feature."},{"level":15,"name":"Superior Critical","desc":"Your weapon attacks score a critical hit on a roll of 18–20."},{"level":18,"name":"Survivor","desc":"At the start of each of your turns, if you have fewer than half your hit point maximum remaining, you regain HP equal to 5 + your Constitution modifier (only when not at 0 HP)."}]},{"name":"Champion (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024 Champion with Remarkable Athlete expanded and Survivor made more reliable.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Improved Critical","desc":"Your weapon attacks score a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20."},{"level":3,"name":"Remarkable Athlete","desc":"Add your Proficiency Bonus to any Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution check that doesn't already use your Proficiency Bonus. You also add your Proficiency Bonus to your Initiative rolls."},{"level":7,"name":"Additional Fighting Style","desc":"Choose a second option from the Fighting Style class feature."},{"level":10,"name":"Heroic Warrior","desc":"At the end of a Short Rest, if you used Second Wind during combat, you gain a Bardic Inspiration–style die (d6) to use on any d20 Test before your next Short or Long Rest."},{"level":15,"name":"Superior Critical","desc":"Your weapon attacks score a critical hit on a roll of 18, 19, or 20."},{"level":18,"name":"Survivor","desc":"At the start of each of your turns, if you have half or fewer of your maximum HP, you regain HP equal to 5 + your Constitution modifier. You don't regain HP from this if you have 0 HP."}]},{"name":"Battle Master (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Battle Masters study the art of combat, mastering a variety of combat maneuvers fueled by superiority dice.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Combat Superiority","desc":"Learn 3 maneuvers (choose from the list). Gain 4 Superiority Dice (d8). Expend a die when using a maneuver. Regain on short/long rest. DC = 8 + prof + Strength or Dexterity modifier."},{"level":3,"name":"Student of War","desc":"Gain proficiency with one type of artisan's tools."},{"level":7,"name":"Know Your Enemy","desc":"Spend 1 minute observing a creature outside combat: learn if it is equal to, better, or worse than you in Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, AC, current HP, Fighter levels, and maneuvers."},{"level":10,"name":"Improved Combat Superiority","desc":"Superiority Dice become d10s."},{"level":15,"name":"Relentless","desc":"When you roll initiative and have no Superiority Dice remaining, you regain 1 Superiority Die."},{"level":18,"name":"Improved Combat Superiority","desc":"Superiority Dice become d12s."}]},{"name":"Battle Master (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024 Battle Master. Know Your Enemy now functions in combat as well.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Combat Superiority","desc":"Learn 3 Maneuvers; gain 4 Superiority Dice (d8). DC = 8 + prof + Strength or Dexterity modifier (your choice)."},{"level":3,"name":"Student of War","desc":"Gain proficiency with one Artisan's Tools of your choice."},{"level":7,"name":"Know Your Enemy","desc":"As a Bonus Action, learn one of the following about a creature you can see: AC, current HP, Hit Point Maximum, Attack Bonus, or Saving Throw modifiers. Proficiency Bonus times per Long Rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Improved Combat Superiority","desc":"Superiority Dice become d10s."},{"level":15,"name":"Relentless","desc":"When you roll Initiative and have no Superiority Dice remaining, you regain 1 die."},{"level":18,"name":"Improved Combat Superiority","desc":"Superiority Dice become d12s."}]},{"name":"Eldritch Knight (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Eldritch Knights supplement their combat with wizard magic, learning spells that enhance their fighting.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Spellcasting","desc":"Learn 2 cantrips and 3 spells from the Wizard list (must be Abjuration or Evocation except for 2 spells). Uses Intelligence modifier."},{"level":3,"name":"Weapon Bond","desc":"Perform a ritual over 1 hour to bond with up to two weapons. Bonded weapons can't be disarmed; you can summon them as a bonus action from any distance on the same plane."},{"level":7,"name":"War Magic","desc":"When you use your action to cast a cantrip, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action."},{"level":10,"name":"Eldritch Strike","desc":"When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, it has disadvantage on its next saving throw against a spell you cast before end of your next turn."},{"level":15,"name":"Arcane Charge","desc":"When you use Action Surge, you can also teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see."},{"level":18,"name":"Improved War Magic","desc":"When you use your action to cast any spell (not just cantrips), you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action."}]},{"name":"Arcane Archer","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Arcane Archers study a blend of archery and arcane magic, imbuing arrows with potent magical effects.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Arcane Archer Lore","desc":"Choose a skill: Arcana or Nature. Gain proficiency. Also learn either Prestidigitation or Druidcraft cantrip."},{"level":3,"name":"Arcane Shot","desc":"Choose 2 Arcane Shot options (learn 1 more at 7th, 10th, 15th, and 18th level). Use 2/short rest. Options include: Banishing Arrow, Beguiling Arrow, Bursting Arrow, Enfeebling Arrow, Grasping Arrow, Piercing Arrow, Seeking Arrow, Shadow Arrow."},{"level":7,"name":"Magic Arrow","desc":"When you fire a nonmagical arrow, it becomes magical for the attack."},{"level":7,"name":"Curving Shot","desc":"When you miss with an Arcane Shot, use a bonus action to reroll the attack against a different target within 60 feet."},{"level":15,"name":"Ever-Ready Shot","desc":"When you roll initiative and have no Arcane Shot uses remaining, regain 1 use."}]},{"name":"Cavalier","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Cavaliers excel at mounted combat, protecting allies and holding the line against enemies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiency","desc":"Gain one skill: Animal Handling, History, Insight, Performance, or Persuasion. Or one language."},{"level":3,"name":"Born to the Saddle","desc":"Advantage on saves vs. being dismounted. Mounting or dismounting costs only 5 feet of movement. Can force a mount fall to land on its feet if it fails a Dexterity check."},{"level":3,"name":"Unwavering Mark","desc":"When you hit with a melee weapon attack, mark the target until start of your next turn. Marked creatures have disadvantage on attacks against anyone other than you. If a marked creature damages a non-you target, use bonus action to make one melee attack against them (adds 1d8/extra die at higher levels). Strength modifier times per long rest."},{"level":7,"name":"Warding Maneuver","desc":"When a creature within 5 feet (or your mount) is hit, use reaction: roll 1d8 and add to their AC for that attack. If they're still hit, they have resistance to the damage. Constitution modifier times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Hold the Line","desc":"Creatures provoke opportunity attacks when moving within 5 feet of you. If you hit, the target's speed becomes 0 until end of turn."},{"level":15,"name":"Ferocious Charger","desc":"When you hit a creature with an opportunity attack (Hold the Line), they must make a Strength save (DC = 8 + prof + Str mod) or be knocked prone."},{"level":18,"name":"Vigilant Defender","desc":"You can make opportunity attacks without using your reaction. Once on each other creature's turn, you can make a special reaction opportunity attack. Can't use your reaction for an OA on the same turn."}]},{"name":"Samurai","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Samurai are warriors of elegance and discipline, fighting with a burning resolve that enables extraordinary performance under pressure.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiency","desc":"Gain proficiency in History, Insight, Performance, or Persuasion. Or learn one language."},{"level":3,"name":"Fighting Spirit","desc":"As a bonus action, gain advantage on weapon attack rolls until end of turn and 5 temp HP (increases to 10 at 10th, 15 at 15th level). Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":7,"name":"Elegant Courtier","desc":"Add Wisdom modifier to Persuasion checks. Proficiency in Wisdom saving throws (or another saving throw if already proficient)."},{"level":10,"name":"Tireless Spirit","desc":"When you roll initiative with no Fighting Spirit uses remaining, regain 1 use."},{"level":15,"name":"Rapid Strike","desc":"If you have advantage on an attack roll, forgo the advantage to make one additional attack (bonus action) against the same target."},{"level":18,"name":"Strength Before Death","desc":"When you are reduced to 0 HP, but not killed outright, delay the effect until end of your next turn. You take a special turn immediately (extra turn). You fall unconscious at the end of this turn if still at 0 HP. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Purple Dragon Knight","source":"Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Purple Dragon Knights (also called Banneret) lead troops with inspiring tactics, boosting allies rather than fighting alone. Sometimes called Banneret outside of Faerûn.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Rallying Cry","desc":"When you use Second Wind, choose up to three creatures within 60 feet that can see or hear you. Each regains HP equal to your Fighter level."},{"level":7,"name":"Royal Envoy","desc":"Proficiency in Persuasion. If already proficient, proficiency bonus doubles for Persuasion. Proficiency in one of Animal Handling, Insight, Intimidation, or Performance."},{"level":10,"name":"Inspiring Surge","desc":"When you use Action Surge, choose one creature within 60 feet that can see or hear you. That creature can make one attack as a reaction."},{"level":15,"name":"Bulwark","desc":"When you use Indomitable to reroll a saving throw, one ally within 60 feet who can see you and who is also affected by the same effect can also reroll their save, using your roll."}]},{"name":"Echo Knight","source":"Explorer's Guide to Wildemount","desc":"Echo Knights draw on dunamancy to summon an echo of themselves from a possible future, fighting alongside it.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Manifest Echo","desc":"Use bonus action to summon an echo (speed 30, AC 14, 1 HP, your saves and immunities). The echo attacks with your melee attacks (at its location, using your modifier). If destroyed or dismissed, use bonus action to resummon it."},{"level":3,"name":"Unleash Incarnation","desc":"Make additional attacks through your echo when you use Extra Attack. Constitution modifier times per long rest."},{"level":7,"name":"Echo Avatar","desc":"As an action, you see and hear through your echo (up to 10 minutes). You are Blinded and Deafened in your own location. Use bonus action to end."},{"level":10,"name":"Shadow Martyr","desc":"When a creature you can see makes an attack roll against a creature (other than you) within 5 feet of your echo, use your reaction to make the echo the target instead. Echo is then destroyed. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":15,"name":"Reclaim Potential","desc":"When your echo is destroyed by taking damage, gain 2d6 temp HP + Constitution modifier. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":18,"name":"Legion of One","desc":"Can maintain two echoes simultaneously. Unleash Incarnation can be used twice per activation."}]},{"name":"Rune Knight","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Rune Knights study giant magic, inscribing runes onto their equipment to gain mystical powers.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with Smith's Tools. Learn Giant language."},{"level":3,"name":"Rune Carver","desc":"Learn 2 runes (Cloud, Stone, Storm, Hill, Fire, Frost; more at higher levels). Each rune can be inscribed on an object; it provides a passive benefit and a power used once per short/long rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Giant's Might","desc":"As a bonus action, become Large size for 1 minute (or Huge if you're Large): weapon damage die goes up one step, advantage on Strength checks and saves. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":7,"name":"Runic Shield","desc":"When another creature you can see within 60 feet is hit by an attack, use your reaction to force the attacker to reroll and use the new result. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Great Stature","desc":"Your runes increase your size permanently by one step (Medium → Large). Your equipment grows with you. Your height increases 1d4 × 4 inches."},{"level":15,"name":"Master of Runes","desc":"You can invoke each rune twice before a short/long rest (was once)."},{"level":18,"name":"Runic Juggernaut","desc":"Giant's Might now makes you Huge (instead of Large). Reach increases by 5 feet. Weapon damage dice increase by two steps while in this form."}]},{"name":"Psi Warrior","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Psi Warriors awaken psychic potential in their mind, using telekinetic and telepathic abilities to augment their fighting.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Psionic Power","desc":"Gain Psionic Energy Dice (d6, amount = twice proficiency bonus). Regain one die on short rest, all on long rest. Use for Psionic Strike, Telekinetic Movement, and Protective Field."},{"level":3,"name":"Psionic Strike","desc":"After hitting with a weapon, expend one Psionic die to deal extra Force damage (die + Intelligence modifier) and possibly push the target 10 feet."},{"level":3,"name":"Telekinetic Movement","desc":"As a bonus action, expend one Psionic die to move a Large or smaller creature or object within 30 feet up to 30 feet in any direction."},{"level":7,"name":"Telekinetic Adept","desc":"Psi-Powered Leap: fly speed = 2× walk speed for 1 turn. Forceful Surge: after a hit, expend Psionic die to push target up to 20 feet (instead of 10)."},{"level":10,"name":"Guarded Mind","desc":"Resistance to Psychic damage. Spend one Psionic die as reaction to end Charmed or Frightened."},{"level":15,"name":"Bulwark of Force","desc":"As bonus action, expend one Psionic die to grant yourself and up to Intelligence modifier creatures within 30 feet half cover for 1 minute."},{"level":18,"name":"Telekinetic Master","desc":"Spend one Psionic die to cast Telekinesis (concentration). While active, use bonus action to make one weapon attack."}]}],"Monk":[{"name":"Way of the Open Hand (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Open Hand Monks are masters of unarmed combat, exploiting every opportunity to unbalance and debilitate foes.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Open Hand Technique","desc":"After hitting with Flurry of Blows, impose one of: prone (Dex save), pushed 15 feet (Str save), or unable to use reactions until end of your next turn (no save)."},{"level":6,"name":"Wholeness of Body","desc":"As an action, regain HP equal to 3× Monk level. Once per long rest."},{"level":11,"name":"Tranquility","desc":"At end of a long rest, gain Sanctuary effect (DC = 8 + prof + Wisdom modifier) until next long rest or until you attack/force a save."},{"level":17,"name":"Quivering Palm","desc":"Spend 3 ki. Hit a creature with unarmed strike to set imperceptible vibrations. At any time within 1 day per Monk level, use action to deal 10d10 necrotic (Con save for half). Only one active at a time."}]},{"name":"Way of the Open Hand (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024 version. Wholeness of Body and Quivering Palm reworked; new Healing Hands feature.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Open Hand Technique","desc":"When you hit with Flurry of Blows, impose one: Prone (Str save), pushed 15 feet (Str save), or can't take Reactions until start of your next turn (no save)."},{"level":3,"name":"Wholeness of Body","desc":"As a Bonus Action, spend 3 Focus Points to heal yourself: roll Martial Arts die + Wisdom modifier. You also end one condition (Blinded, Deafened, or Poisoned) affecting you."},{"level":6,"name":"Fleet Step","desc":"When you take a Bonus Action other than Step of the Wind, you can take Step of the Wind as part of the same Bonus Action."},{"level":11,"name":"Stunning Strike Improvement","desc":"Quivering Palm replaced with enhanced Stunning Strike: a creature stunned by your Stunning Strike is also unable to make death saving throws while Stunned."},{"level":17,"name":"Quivering Palm","desc":"Spend 4 Focus Points. Hit with an unarmed strike; the target must make a Constitution save or be reduced to 0 HP. On a success, take 10d10 Necrotic."}]},{"name":"Way of Shadow (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Shadow Monks follow darkness and silence, excelling at stealth and ambush.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Shadow Arts","desc":"Spend 2 ki to cast Darkness, Darkvision, Pass without Trace, or Silence (no spell slots required)."},{"level":6,"name":"Shadow Step","desc":"When in dim light or darkness, teleport as bonus action up to 60 feet to another spot in dim light or darkness. Advantage on first melee attack this turn."},{"level":11,"name":"Cloak of Shadows","desc":"In dim light or darkness, use action to become invisible until you attack, cast a spell, or enter bright light."},{"level":17,"name":"Opportunist","desc":"When a creature within 5 feet is hit by an attack by someone other than you, use your reaction to make a melee attack against that creature."}]},{"name":"Way of the Four Elements (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Four Elements Monks discipline their bodies and minds to manipulate the primal elements: fire, water, air, and earth.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Disciple of the Elements","desc":"Learn elemental disciplines (spend ki to create elemental effects). Start with 2 disciplines; learn one more at 6th, 11th, and 17th level. Examples: Fist of Unbroken Air (push + damage with ki), Ride the Wind (Fly), Sweeping Cinder Strike (Burning Hands), Rush of the Gale Spirits (Gust of Wind), Shape the Flowing River (control water/ice), Clench of the North Wind (Hold Person), Water Whip (pull + bludgeoning), Earth Tremors (Earthquake partial), etc."},{"level":3,"name":"Elemental Attunement","desc":"Free discipline usable at will: create small elemental effects like lighting a candle, pushing a small object, etc."}]},{"name":"Way of the Long Death","source":"Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Long Death Monks are obsessed with the meaning and mechanics of dying, channeling death energy to terrify and drain enemies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Touch of Death","desc":"When you reduce a creature within 5 feet to 0 HP, gain temp HP = Wisdom modifier + Monk level."},{"level":6,"name":"Hour of Reaping","desc":"As an action, all creatures within 30 feet make a Wisdom save or are Frightened of you until end of your next turn."},{"level":11,"name":"Mastery of Death","desc":"Spend 1 ki when reduced to 0 HP to have 1 HP instead."},{"level":17,"name":"Touch of the Long Death","desc":"As an action, spend 1–10 ki. Target within 5 feet makes a Con save. Fail: take 2d10 necrotic per ki spent. Success: take half."}]},{"name":"Way of the Sun Soul","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything / Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Sun Soul Monks channel inner fire into bursts of radiant and fire energy, ranged attacks that complement their martial arts.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Radiant Sun Bolt","desc":"Gain a ranged spell attack (30/60 ft, 1d4+Dex radiant). You can spend 1 ki to make two extra bolt attacks as bonus action."},{"level":6,"name":"Searing Arc Strike","desc":"After an Attack action with unarmed or monk weapon, spend 2 ki to cast Burning Hands (save DC = ki save DC)."},{"level":11,"name":"Searing Sunburst","desc":"As an action, spend 0–3 ki to create a 20-ft radius sphere of light (60 ft range). Creatures in sphere: Con save or take 2d6 radiant (+ 2d6 per extra ki spent)."},{"level":17,"name":"Sun Shield","desc":"Emit bright light 30 ft / dim 30 ft beyond. Reaction when hit in melee: deal 5 + Wisdom modifier radiant to the attacker. Toggle light on/off as bonus action."}]},{"name":"Way of the Kensei","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Kensei Monks treat weapons as an extension of their body and mind, training to become one with their chosen blades.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Path of the Kensei","desc":"Choose 2 weapons as Kensei Weapons (one must be ranged; can be added to at levels 6, 11, 17). Kensei weapons are monk weapons for you. One-handed Kensei melee weapon: +2 AC when attacking with it (use bonus action). Ranged: don't run out of ammunition."},{"level":3,"name":"Agile Parry","desc":"If you make an unarmed strike as part of the Attack action and aren't wielding a shield, gain +2 AC until start of your next turn."},{"level":6,"name":"Kensei's Shot","desc":"As a bonus action, your ranged Kensei weapon attacks deal +1d4 damage this turn."},{"level":6,"name":"Way of the Brush","desc":"Gain proficiency with calligrapher's supplies or painter's supplies."},{"level":11,"name":"Sharpen the Blade","desc":"As a bonus action, spend 1–3 ki. Kensei weapon gains +1/+2/+3 to attack and damage rolls for 1 minute."},{"level":17,"name":"Unerring Accuracy","desc":"Once per turn, if you miss with a monk weapon attack, reroll the attack."}]},{"name":"Way of the Drunken Master","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Drunken Masters adopt a fighting style that mimics a drunk's stumbling, making them unpredictable and hard to pin down.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency in Performance and Brewer's Supplies."},{"level":3,"name":"Drunken Technique","desc":"When using Flurry of Blows, gain benefit of Disengage action and move speed increases by 10 feet until end of turn."},{"level":6,"name":"Tipsy Sway","desc":"Leap to Your Feet: stand up from prone using only 5 feet of movement (instead of half speed). Redirect Attack: when missed by a melee attack, spend 1 ki to redirect the attack to another creature within 5 feet of you."},{"level":11,"name":"Drunkard's Luck","desc":"When you make an attack roll, ability check, or save with disadvantage, spend 2 ki to remove the disadvantage."},{"level":17,"name":"Intoxicated Frenzy","desc":"When using Flurry of Blows, make 3 additional attacks (max 5 Flurry attacks per turn) if each hits a different target."}]},{"name":"Way of Mercy","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Mercy Monks learn to manipulate life force, healing allies and harvesting vitality from enemies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Implements of Mercy","desc":"Proficiency in Insight and Medicine. Herbalism Kit proficiency. Gain a mask as a bonus item (worn as focus for features)."},{"level":3,"name":"Hand of Harm","desc":"Once per turn when you hit with an unarmed strike, spend 1 ki to deal extra Necrotic damage equal to Martial Arts die + Wisdom modifier. Target also contracts a random disease (DM's choice) if you so choose."},{"level":3,"name":"Hand of Healing","desc":"As an action, spend 1 ki to touch a creature; restore HP equal to Martial Arts die + Wisdom modifier. Can end Blinded, Deafened, Paralyzed, Poisoned, or Stunned."},{"level":6,"name":"Physician's Touch","desc":"Hand of Harm: also Poison condition (Con save). Hand of Healing: also cures one condition listed above plus Diseased."},{"level":11,"name":"Flurry of Healing and Harm","desc":"Use Flurry of Blows to make unarmed strikes or Hand of Healing touches (instead of attacks). Each touch heals as Hand of Healing but costs no ki."},{"level":17,"name":"Hand of Ultimate Mercy","desc":"Spend 5 ki to cast Raise Dead (no material components). Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Way of the Astral Self","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Astral Self Monks summon a spectral visage of their astral form that extends beyond the physical body.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Arms of the Astral Self","desc":"Spend 1 ki (bonus action) to summon spectral arms for 10 minutes. Arms count as monk weapons (reach 5 ft). Force damage. Can make 2 arm attacks using your bonus action if you took the Attack action."},{"level":6,"name":"Visage of the Astral Self","desc":"Spend 1 ki (bonus action) to summon astral visage for 10 minutes. Advantages: see normally in darkness (10 ft), understand and be understood in any spoken language, Intimidation and Insight advantage."},{"level":11,"name":"Body of the Astral Self","desc":"If both Arms and Visage are active, summon astral body: reaction to halve damage when hit (once per turn), astral arms deal 2d10 force damage in a 10 ft cone on Bonus Action attack (instead of individual attacks)."},{"level":17,"name":"Awakened Astral Self","desc":"Fully manifest astral self: +2 AC, attacks with arms deal extra 1d10 force, can spend 5 ki to summon full astral body (body gives bonus attacks)."}]}],"Paladin":[{"name":"Oath of Devotion (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Devotion Paladins embody the ideal knightly champion—honorable, brave, and unwavering in their commitment to justice.","tenets":["Be honest in word and deed.","Protect the weak and punish those who threaten them.","Act with courage.","Show compassion to others."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Sacred Weapon","desc":"Channel Divinity: imbue one weapon with holy power for 1 minute. Add Charisma modifier to attack rolls. Weapon sheds bright light (20 ft) and dim light (20 ft beyond). If undead or fiend, also frightened."},{"level":3,"name":"Turn the Unholy","desc":"Channel Divinity: as an action, present holy symbol. Fiends and Undead within 30 feet make Wisdom save or are Turned for 1 minute."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Devotion","desc":"You and friendly creatures within 10 feet (30 ft at level 18) are immune to the Charmed condition."},{"level":15,"name":"Purity of Spirit","desc":"Always under the effect of Protection from Evil and Good."},{"level":20,"name":"Holy Nimbus","desc":"As an action, emit a 30-ft aura of sunlight for 1 minute. Enemies in the aura take 10 radiant at start of their turns. Advantage on saving throws vs. spells from fiends and undead. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of Devotion (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Sacred Weapon now deals Radiant damage; Aura of Devotion enhanced.","tenets":["Let your word be your promise.","Protect the weak and never fear to act.","Let your deeds be an example to all."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Sacred Weapon","desc":"Channel Divinity: as a Bonus Action, imbue one weapon you're holding with positive energy. For 1 minute, add Charisma modifier to attack rolls, deal Radiant damage on hits, and emit bright light 20 feet (dim 20 more)."},{"level":3,"name":"Holy Rebuke","desc":"When an enemy hits you, you can use your Reaction to deal Radiant damage equal to your Proficiency Bonus to the attacker."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Devotion","desc":"You and allies within 10 feet (30 feet at 18th) are immune to the Charmed condition while you're Conscious."},{"level":15,"name":"Smite of Protection","desc":"Your Divine Smite now grants half cover to all allies within 30 feet until start of your next turn."},{"level":20,"name":"Holy Nimbus","desc":"As a Bonus Action, emit 30-foot aura of sunlight for 1 minute. Enemies in aura take 10 Radiant at start of their turns and have Disadvantage on saving throws vs. your spells. Once per Long Rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of the Ancients (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Ancients Paladins take sides with the forces of light and life, pledging to preserve beauty and joy in the world.","tenets":["Kindle the light of hope.","Shelter life.","Delight in song and laughter.","Be the light in the darkness."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Nature's Wrath","desc":"Channel Divinity: spectral vines sprout from the ground. One creature within 10 feet makes a Strength or Dexterity save (their choice) or is Restrained until freed (strength check vs. DC or channel divinity again)."},{"level":3,"name":"Turn the Faithless","desc":"Channel Divinity: fey and fiends within 30 feet make Wisdom save or are Turned for 1 minute."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Warding","desc":"You and allies within 10 feet (30 at 18th) have resistance to damage from spells."},{"level":15,"name":"Undying Sentinel","desc":"When reduced to 0 HP, drop to 1 HP instead. Once per long rest. Don't suffer age penalties magically; can't be magically aged."},{"level":20,"name":"Elder Champion","desc":"As an action, transform for 1 minute. Regain 10 HP at start of each turn. Cast spells as bonus action. Enemies within 10 feet have disadvantage on saves vs. your paladin spells and Channel Divinity. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of Vengeance (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Vengeance Paladins are relentless hunters of evildoers, pursuing one goal above all: punish the wicked.","tenets":["Fight the greater evil.","No mercy for the wicked.","By any means necessary.","Restitution."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Abjure Enemy","desc":"Channel Divinity: one creature within 60 feet makes a Wisdom save or is Frightened and speed drops to 0 for 1 minute (undead and fiends have disadvantage on save)."},{"level":3,"name":"Vow of Enmity","desc":"Channel Divinity: as bonus action, swear enmity vs. one creature within 10 feet. Advantage on attack rolls against it for 1 minute."},{"level":7,"name":"Relentless Avenger","desc":"When you hit with an opportunity attack, reduce enemy speed to 0 until end of turn and move up to half your speed (no opportunity attacks) immediately after."},{"level":15,"name":"Soul of Vengeance","desc":"When a creature under your Vow of Enmity makes an attack, use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against it."},{"level":20,"name":"Avenging Angel","desc":"As an action, transform into an angelic avenger for 1 hour. Fly speed 60 ft. Enemies within 30 feet must make Wisdom save or be Frightened for 1 minute. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of Conquest","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Conquest Paladins crush their enemies beneath iron fists, spreading fear and demanding submission.","tenets":["Douse the flames of hope.","Rule with an iron fist.","Strength above all."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Conquering Presence","desc":"Channel Divinity: all creatures of your choice within 30 feet must make a Wisdom save or be Frightened for 1 minute."},{"level":3,"name":"Guided Strike","desc":"Channel Divinity: gain +10 bonus to an attack roll. Can be used after seeing the roll but before knowing success."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Conquest","desc":"Frightened creatures within your aura (10 ft, 30 ft at 18th) have speed 0 and take psychic damage = half your Paladin level at start of their turns."},{"level":15,"name":"Scornful Rebuke","desc":"When damaged while not Incapacitated, deal psychic damage (Charisma modifier) to the attacker."},{"level":20,"name":"Invincible Conqueror","desc":"As an action, transform for 1 minute: resistance to all damage, extra attack per Attack action, and critical hits on 19–20. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of Redemption","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Redemption Paladins seek to bring even the most dangerous evildoers to justice through peaceful means before resorting to violence.","tenets":["Peace.","Innocence.","Patience.","Wisdom."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Emissary of Peace","desc":"+5 to Persuasion checks (always)."},{"level":3,"name":"Rebuke the Violent","desc":"Channel Divinity: when you see a creature within 30 feet deal damage with an attack, use your reaction to force the attacker to make a Wisdom save or take the same damage (radiant type)."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of the Guardian","desc":"When an ally within 10 feet (30 at 18th) takes damage, use your reaction to take that damage instead."},{"level":15,"name":"Protective Spirit","desc":"At end of each of your turns, if below half HP, regain HP equal to 1d6 + half Paladin level (not while Incapacitated)."},{"level":20,"name":"Emissary of Redemption","desc":"Resistance to all damage from creatures. When a creature damages you, they take radiant damage = half the damage dealt. Ends if you attack or force saves on a creature."}]},{"name":"Oath of Glory","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Mythic Odysseys of Theros","desc":"Glory Paladins are living embodiments of heroism, inspiring allies with their legendary deeds.","tenets":["Actions over words.","Courage.","Uphold others.","Hone the body."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Inspiring Smite","desc":"After using Divine Smite, use bonus action to distribute temp HP (2d8 + Paladin level) among creatures within 30 feet (yourself included)."},{"level":3,"name":"Peerless Athlete","desc":"Channel Divinity: advantage on Athletics and Acrobatics; carry capacity doubles; jump distance doubles; for 10 minutes."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Alacrity","desc":"You and allies starting their turn within 10 feet (30 at 18th) gain +10 speed for that turn."},{"level":15,"name":"Glorious Defense","desc":"When an ally within 30 feet is hit, use reaction to add Charisma modifier to their AC for that attack. If the attack misses as a result, make one weapon attack against the attacker (if in range)."},{"level":20,"name":"Living Legend","desc":"For 1 minute: Charisma checks and saves have advantage; once per turn, if you miss a weapon attack, reroll and use the new roll; failed saving throws can be rerolled once. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oath of the Watchers","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Watchers Paladins guard mortal realms against extraplanar threats—aberrations, celestials, elementals, fey, and fiends.","tenets":["Vigilance.","Loyalty.","Discipline."],"features":[{"level":3,"name":"Watcher's Will","desc":"Channel Divinity: Charisma modifier times targets within 30 feet (yourself included) gain advantage on Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma saving throws for 1 minute."},{"level":3,"name":"Abjure the Extraplanar","desc":"Channel Divinity: present holy symbol; aberrations, celestials, elementals, fey, and fiends within 30 feet make Wisdom save or are Turned for 1 minute."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of the Sentinel","desc":"Add proficiency bonus to initiative rolls for you and allies within 10 feet (30 at 18th)."},{"level":15,"name":"Vigilant Rebuke","desc":"When you or an ally within 30 feet succeeds a save vs. extraplanar creature's magic, use your reaction to deal 2d8 + Charisma modifier force damage to the caster."},{"level":20,"name":"Mortal Bulwark","desc":"For 1 minute: advantage on attack rolls vs. aberrations, celestials, elementals, fey, fiends. Immunity to Charmed and Frightened. If you hit one of those creature types, you can banish it (Charisma save DC = spell save DC; if it fails, it's banished to its home plane). Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Oathbreaker","source":"Dungeon Master's Guide 2014 / 2024","desc":"Oathbreakers are paladins who broke their sacred oath and now serve darker powers. Typically an NPC option or for dark campaigns.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Control Undead","desc":"Target one undead within 30 feet; it makes Wisdom save or falls under your control for 24 hours. Can't have more controlled than Charisma modifier."},{"level":3,"name":"Channel Divinity: Dreadful Aspect","desc":"Each creature of your choice within 30 feet makes Wisdom save or is Frightened of you for 1 minute."},{"level":7,"name":"Aura of Hate","desc":"You and nearby fiends and undead (10 ft, 30 at 18th) add Charisma modifier to melee weapon attack damage."},{"level":15,"name":"Supernatural Resistance","desc":"Resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical weapons."},{"level":20,"name":"Dread Lord","desc":"As an action, create a 30-ft aura of darkness for 1 minute. The aura reduces bright light to dim. Enemies that start turns in it take 4d10 psychic. Attack rolls inside have disadvantage unless the attacker has darkvision. Once per long rest."}]}],"Ranger":[{"name":"Hunter (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Hunters are the classic rangers, learning to hunt the most dangerous quarry with a variety of tactical options.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Hunter's Prey","desc":"Choose one: Colossus Slayer (1d8 bonus vs. damaged target below max HP, once per turn), Giant Killer (reaction attack when a Large+ creature misses you), or Horde Breaker (attack a second adjacent creature with same weapon once per turn)."},{"level":7,"name":"Defensive Tactics","desc":"Choose one: Escape the Horde (OA against you have disadvantage), Multiattack Defense (+4 AC after being hit, until end of turn), or Steel Will (advantage vs. Frightened)."},{"level":11,"name":"Multiattack","desc":"Choose one: Volley (action: ranged attack vs. all creatures in 10 ft radius within range) or Whirlwind Attack (action: melee attack vs. all creatures within 5 ft)."},{"level":15,"name":"Superior Hunter's Defense","desc":"Choose one: Evasion (Dex save half = zero damage), Stand Against the Tide (when melee attack misses, redirect to adjacent creature), or Uncanny Dodge (reaction: halve damage from one attack)."}]},{"name":"Hunter (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Hunter's Prey and Defensive Tactics options streamlined.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Hunter's Prey","desc":"Choose one option: Colossus Slayer (extra 1d8 damage to a target below max HP once per turn), Giant Killer (react to attack when Large+ misses you), or Horde Breaker (hit a second target within 5 feet of the first, using the same weapon, once per turn)."},{"level":7,"name":"Defensive Tactics","desc":"Choose one option: Escape the Horde (opportunity attacks against you have Disadvantage), Multiattack Defense (+4 AC after being hit, until end of turn), or Steel Will (advantage on saves vs. Frightened)."},{"level":11,"name":"Hunter's Lore","desc":"When you hit with a weapon attack, you learn if the target has any immunities, resistances, or vulnerabilities to damage types."},{"level":15,"name":"Superior Hunter's Defense","desc":"Evasion: Dex save = no damage (half = half). Or choose Uncanny Dodge (reaction: halve damage)."}]},{"name":"Beast Master (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Beast Masters forge deep bonds with a beast companion, fighting alongside it in combat.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Ranger's Companion","desc":"Choose a Beast of CR ≤ 1/4 that isn't flying or swimming. It obeys your commands. Uses your proficiency bonus for attacks/saves. Each turn: Bonus Action to command it Attack; otherwise takes Dodge action."},{"level":7,"name":"Exceptional Training","desc":"Your companion can Dash, Disengage, or Help instead of attacking on turns you command it."},{"level":11,"name":"Bestial Fury","desc":"When commanded to attack, companion can make two attacks."},{"level":15,"name":"Share Spells","desc":"When you cast a spell targeting yourself, the beast companion is also affected."}]},{"name":"Beast Master (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Primal Companion replaces specific beast choice with three stat-block options.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Primal Companion","desc":"Summon a Primal Beast (Beast of the Land, Beast of the Sea, or Beast of the Sky) as a Bonus Action. It obeys commands; uses your Proficiency Bonus. You can expend a spell slot to revive it (1 HP). Stats are fixed per beast type."},{"level":7,"name":"Exceptional Training","desc":"When you use your Bonus Action to command the beast, you can also have it take the Dash, Disengage, Dodge, or Help action."},{"level":11,"name":"Bestial Fury","desc":"The beast can make 2 attacks when commanded to attack."},{"level":15,"name":"Share Spells","desc":"When you cast a self-targeting spell, you can also have the beast affected by it."}]},{"name":"Gloom Stalker","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Gloom Stalkers haunt the darkness, hunting their enemies before those enemies even know they're being hunted.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Dread Ambusher","desc":"Add Wisdom modifier to initiative. In first round of combat: extra attack on Attack action; that attack deals 1d8 extra damage."},{"level":3,"name":"Umbral Sight","desc":"Darkvision 60 ft. Creatures relying on darkvision can't see you in darkness."},{"level":7,"name":"Iron Mind","desc":"Proficiency in Wisdom saving throws (or if already proficient, choose Intelligence or Charisma)."},{"level":11,"name":"Stalker's Flurry","desc":"Once per turn when you miss with an attack, make another attack."},{"level":15,"name":"Shadowy Dodge","desc":"When a creature misses you with an attack, use your reaction to move up to half your speed and become invisible until start of next turn (if in dim or dark light)."}]},{"name":"Horizon Walker","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Horizon Walkers guard the borders between planes, becoming walking conduits of planar energy.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Detect Portal","desc":"Sense the presence of planar portals within 1 mile (action, once per short/long rest)."},{"level":3,"name":"Planar Warrior","desc":"When you Attack, choose a creature within 30 feet. Your first attack deals extra Force damage (1d8 at 11th: 2d8) and is magical, and no longer deals other damage types for that hit."},{"level":7,"name":"Ethereal Step","desc":"At start of your turn, cast Etherealness (lasts until end of turn). Once per short/long rest."},{"level":11,"name":"Distant Strike","desc":"When using Attack action, teleport up to 10 feet before each attack. Third attack can target a different creature from the first two."},{"level":15,"name":"Spectral Defense","desc":"When you take damage, use reaction to become resistant to that damage type until start of next turn."}]},{"name":"Monster Slayer","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Monster Slayers are specialists in hunting powerful supernatural threats—dragons, vampires, demons, and other terrible beings.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Hunter's Sense","desc":"As an action, learn about a creature within 60 feet: immunities, resistances, vulnerabilities. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Slayer's Prey","desc":"As bonus action, mark a creature within 60 feet. Your first hit with a weapon attack each turn deals +1d6 damage. Once per turn. Lasts until mark ends or you use on another creature."},{"level":7,"name":"Supernatural Defense","desc":"Advantage on saves forced by your Slayer's Prey target. Add 1d6 to saves vs. magic from that target."},{"level":11,"name":"Magic-User's Nemesis","desc":"When you see a creature casting a spell or teleporting within 60 ft, use reaction: creature makes Wisdom save (DC = spell save DC) or have casting/teleporting interrupted."},{"level":15,"name":"Slayer's Counter","desc":"When the Slayer's Prey target forces you to make a saving throw, use reaction to make one weapon attack against it. If it hits, auto-succeed on the save."}]},{"name":"Fey Wanderer","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Fey Wanderers carry the mark of the Feywild and its captivating, maddening magic.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Dreadful Strikes","desc":"Once per turn on a hit, deal extra 1d4 Psychic damage. Increases to 1d6 at 11th level."},{"level":3,"name":"Fey Wanderer Magic","desc":"Charm Person and additional spells always prepared based on level. At 3rd: Charm Person; 5th: Misty Step; 9th: Dispel Magic; 13th: Dimension Door; 17th: Mislead."},{"level":3,"name":"Otherworldly Glamour","desc":"Add Wisdom modifier to Charisma checks."},{"level":7,"name":"Beguiling Twist","desc":"Advantage on saves vs. Charmed and Frightened. When a creature within 120 feet succeeds on such a save, use your reaction to target another creature and impose Charmed or Frightened for 1 minute (Wisdom save to resist)."},{"level":11,"name":"Fey Reinforcements","desc":"Once per long rest (or spell slot), cast Summon Fey."},{"level":15,"name":"Misty Presence","desc":"Once per long rest (or 4th+ spell slot), cast Seeming on self; become hidden in fey glamour; can move through creature spaces; immune to opportunity attacks for 24 hours."}]},{"name":"Swarmkeeper","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Swarmkeepers attract a magical swarm of nature spirits that surrounds them, obeying their commands.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Gathered Swarm","desc":"Surround yourself with a swarm of spirits. Once per turn on a hit, choose one: move target 15 ft (Str save to resist), gain 1d6 temp HP (no save), or move yourself 5 ft without provoking OAs."},{"level":3,"name":"Swarmkeeper Magic","desc":"Always prepared spells: Mage Hand (bonus action); 5th: Web; 9th: Gaseous Form; 13th: Arcane Eye; 17th: Insect Plague."},{"level":7,"name":"Writhing Tide","desc":"Once per short/long rest, fly speed 10 ft for 1 minute when on your turn."},{"level":11,"name":"Mighty Swarm","desc":"Gathered Swarm effects improved: push 30 ft or restrain until end of next turn (no temp HP), or move yourself 10 ft. Also knocks prone on push."},{"level":15,"name":"Swarming Dispersal","desc":"When you take damage, use reaction to turn into a swarm: teleport up to 30 feet; resistance to the triggering damage. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."}]}],"Rogue":[{"name":"Thief (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Thieves hone skills that let them get into and out of trouble, earning their living as burglars, assassins, cutpurses, and con artists.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Fast Hands","desc":"Use the bonus action from Cunning Action to make a Sleight of Hand check, use thieves' tools, or take the Use an Object action."},{"level":3,"name":"Second-Story Work","desc":"Climbing costs no extra movement. Running jump distance increases by Dexterity modifier feet."},{"level":9,"name":"Supreme Sneak","desc":"Advantage on Stealth checks when moving no more than half speed in the same turn."},{"level":13,"name":"Use Magic Device","desc":"Ignore all class, race, and level requirements for magic item usage."},{"level":17,"name":"Thief's Reflexes","desc":"Take two turns in first combat round: first on initiative count, second on initiative count - 10."}]},{"name":"Thief (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Fast Hands now includes magic item activation. Thief's Reflexes reworked.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Fast Hands","desc":"As a Bonus Action, make a Sleight of Hand check, use thieves' tools to disarm a trap or open a lock, take the Help action, or take the Use an Object action (including activating a magic item that normally requires an action, like drinking a potion)."},{"level":3,"name":"Second-Story Work","desc":"Climbing doesn't cost extra movement. You add your Dexterity modifier to the distance covered by a running long jump."},{"level":9,"name":"Supreme Sneak","desc":"You gain the Cunning Strike option: Stealth Attack (your movement this turn doesn't expend your Speed; make a Dexterity check to move without being noticed)."},{"level":13,"name":"Use Magic Device","desc":"Ignore class, race, and level restrictions on magic item use. Can attune to up to 4 items (instead of 3)."},{"level":17,"name":"Thief's Reflexes","desc":"In the first round of each combat, you can take an additional Bonus Action on your turn."}]},{"name":"Assassin (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Assassins focus on dealing massive damage to a surprised foe, using stealth and disguise to set up a killing blow.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with disguise kit and poisoner's kit."},{"level":3,"name":"Assassinate","desc":"Advantage on attacks against creatures that haven't taken a turn in combat yet. Auto-critical hit on surprised creatures."},{"level":9,"name":"Infiltration Expertise","desc":"Spend 7 days and 25 gp to create a false identity. Can establish credentials and create a cover story. Also, learn to mimic another's handwriting or speech patterns after 3 hours of study."},{"level":13,"name":"Impostor","desc":"Unerringly mimic another person's speech, writing, and behavior. Must study subject for 3 hours. Insight contested by your Deception."},{"level":17,"name":"Death Strike","desc":"When you hit a surprised creature, it makes a Constitution save (DC = 8 + prof + Dex mod) or takes double damage."}]},{"name":"Assassin (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Assassinate now triggers on Initiative advantage. New Subtle Strikes feature.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Bonus Proficiencies","desc":"Proficiency with disguise kit and poisoner's kit."},{"level":3,"name":"Assassinate","desc":"You have Advantage on attack rolls against any creature that hasn't taken a turn in combat yet. You also deal extra damage (Proficiency Bonus) on hits against creatures that have the Surprised condition."},{"level":3,"name":"Assassin's Tools","desc":"You have a Disguise Kit and a Poisoner's Kit, and gain the Crafting Poison downtime activity."},{"level":9,"name":"Infiltration Expertise","desc":"You can create false identities for yourself. After spending 1 week and 25 gp, you have Expertise in Deception checks to pass off your false identity."},{"level":13,"name":"Impostor","desc":"After spending 3 hours studying a Humanoid, you can mimic their speech, writing, and behavior. Your disguise is perfect; Insight checks against your Deception are made at Disadvantage."},{"level":17,"name":"Death Strike","desc":"When you score a Critical Hit, the target makes a Constitution save (DC = 8 + Proficiency Bonus + Dexterity modifier) or is reduced to 0 HP."}]},{"name":"Arcane Trickster (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Arcane Tricksters enhance their roguish abilities with illusion and enchantment magic from the wizard spell list.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Spellcasting","desc":"Learn 3 spells from Wizard list (must be Enchantment or Illusion, except for 2 spells) and 2 Wizard cantrips (one must be Mage Hand). Uses Intelligence."},{"level":3,"name":"Mage Hand Legerdemain","desc":"Mage Hand is invisible. Can use Cunning Action to control it. Can use it to: pick locks, disarm traps, pick pockets, plant objects. Sleight of Hand vs. Perception."},{"level":9,"name":"Magical Ambush","desc":"If you're hidden when you cast a spell, the target has disadvantage on saving throws vs. the spell this turn."},{"level":13,"name":"Versatile Trickster","desc":"Use bonus action to have Mage Hand distract a creature within 5 feet of it. Advantage on attacks against that creature until end of turn."},{"level":17,"name":"Spell Thief","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet casts a spell, use your reaction to steal it: force Int save (DC = 8 + prof + Int mod). Fail: lose the spell; you gain it and can cast it within 8 hours."}]},{"name":"Mastermind","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything / Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Masterminds are tacticians who command allies, gather intelligence, and manipulate others from behind the scenes.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Master of Intrigue","desc":"Proficiency with disguise kit, forgery kit, one gaming set. Learn two languages. Can mimic speech and accents after hearing them 1 minute."},{"level":3,"name":"Master of Tactics","desc":"Take Help action as bonus action. Can Help a creature up to 30 feet away on attack rolls (instead of 5 feet), as long as your target is in range of the creature you're helping."},{"level":9,"name":"Insightful Manipulator","desc":"Spend 1 minute observing a creature. Learn if it is your equal, superior, or inferior in: Intelligence, Wisdom, Charisma, and class levels (if any)."},{"level":13,"name":"Misdirection","desc":"When a creature can see you, use Cunning Action to have another creature within 5 feet (that can be seen) become the apparent target; they are treated as if they were you for perception and attack targeting until your next turn."},{"level":17,"name":"Soul of Deceit","desc":"Can't be compelled to tell the truth by magic. Insight checks to determine truthfulness find you truthful even when lying."}]},{"name":"Swashbuckler","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything / Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Swashbucklers move with the daring and panache of a pirate or dashing duelist, relying on speed and style.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Fancy Footwork","desc":"When you make a melee attack in your turn against a creature, that creature can't make opportunity attacks against you this turn."},{"level":3,"name":"Rakish Audacity","desc":"Add Charisma modifier to Initiative. Can Sneak Attack with a melee weapon even if no ally is adjacent, as long as no other enemies are adjacent to you."},{"level":9,"name":"Panache","desc":"Use bonus action and Persuasion check (contested by Insight): against an enemy, it must attack only you (Charmed until start of your next turn or if you/allies harm it); against a non-hostile, they are charmed for 1 minute."},{"level":13,"name":"Elegant Maneuver","desc":"Use bonus action to gain advantage on your next Athletics or Acrobatics check."},{"level":17,"name":"Master Duelist","desc":"When you miss with an attack, you can reroll it with advantage. Once per short/long rest."}]},{"name":"Inquisitive","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Inquisitives are detectives, hunters, and investigators who read opponents like an open book and exploit every weakness.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Ear for Deceit","desc":"Minimum roll of 8 on Insight checks (before adding modifiers)."},{"level":3,"name":"Eye for Detail","desc":"Bonus action to make Perception or Investigation check."},{"level":3,"name":"Insightful Fighting","desc":"Bonus action: make Insight check vs. creature's Deception check. Success: Sneak Attack applies against that creature even if no ally is adjacent, for 1 minute or until another creature is targeted."},{"level":9,"name":"Steady Eye","desc":"If you don't move this turn, advantage on Perception and Investigation."},{"level":13,"name":"Unerring Eye","desc":"As action, detect magical deceptions (invisible creatures, illusions, shapechanger disguises) within 30 feet. Wisdom modifier times per long rest."},{"level":17,"name":"Eye for Weakness","desc":"While Insightful Fighting is active against a creature, Sneak Attack dice increase by 3d6 against that creature."}]},{"name":"Scout","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Scouts are skilled in wilderness survival and stealth, acting as advance agents for larger forces.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Skirmisher","desc":"When an enemy ends its turn within 5 feet of you, use your reaction to move up to half your speed (doesn't provoke opportunity attacks)."},{"level":3,"name":"Survivalist","desc":"Gain proficiency in Nature and Survival. Proficiency bonus doubles for those skills."},{"level":9,"name":"Superior Mobility","desc":"Speed increases by 10 feet. Climbing and swimming speeds also increase by 10 feet."},{"level":13,"name":"Ambush Master","desc":"Advantage on initiative. If you go first, all allies have advantage on attacks vs. any creature you attack in the first round."},{"level":17,"name":"Sudden Strike","desc":"When you take the Attack action, you can make an additional attack (bonus action). This attack can also Sneak Attack; but only one Sneak Attack per turn total."}]},{"name":"Phantom","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Phantoms walk the line between the living and the dead, drawing on the knowledge of dead souls.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Whispers of the Dead","desc":"When you finish a short or long rest, choose one skill or tool proficiency from a dead creature nearby. Gain that proficiency until next rest."},{"level":3,"name":"Wails from the Grave","desc":"Immediately after Sneak Attack, deal extra necrotic damage (half Sneak Attack dice, rounded up) to a second creature within 30 feet of the first. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":9,"name":"Tokens of the Departed","desc":"When a creature dies within 30 feet, capture its soul (tiny trinket). While holding it: proficiency in Death saving throws, Speak with Dead (target = dead creature that produced the token). Can have up to proficiency bonus trinkets."},{"level":13,"name":"Ghost Walk","desc":"Assume ghostly form (bonus action): fly speed 10 ft, can move through objects (can't end there), resistance to nonmagical B/P/S. Lasts 10 minutes. Once per long rest (or token use)."},{"level":17,"name":"Death's Friend","desc":"Wails from the Grave no longer costs a use. When you use it, your Sneak Attack also applies to the necrotic hit. Once per round."}]},{"name":"Soulknife","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Soulknives strike with blades of pure psychic energy, connecting with others telepathically.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Psionic Power","desc":"Gain Psionic Energy Dice (d6, amount = twice proficiency bonus). Regain 1 die on short rest; all on long rest. Used for Psi-Bolstered Knack, Psychic Whispers, and Psychic Blades bonus damage."},{"level":3,"name":"Psychic Blades","desc":"Manifest blades of psychic energy (free action on attack): 1d6 psychic damage per blade (off-hand costs bonus action, deals 1d4). Finesse, thrown (60 ft). Disappear after attack. No material cost."},{"level":9,"name":"Soul Blades","desc":"Homing Strikes: expend a die to reroll a Psychic Blade attack. Psychic Teleportation: as bonus action, expend a die and teleport up to 10× the roll result in feet."},{"level":13,"name":"Psychic Veil","desc":"As action, become invisible for 1 hour. Ends if you attack, force save, or deal damage. Once per long rest (or Psionic die)."},{"level":17,"name":"Rend Mind","desc":"When you use Psychic Blades and hit a creature, spend 3 Psionic dice: target makes Wisdom save (DC = 8 + prof + Dex mod) or is Stunned until end of your next turn."}]}],"Sorcerer":[{"name":"Draconic Bloodline (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Draconic sorcerers have dragon blood somewhere in their ancestry, granting them magical affinity to a chromatic or metallic dragon.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Dragon Ancestor","desc":"Choose a dragon type (Black/Acid, Blue/Lightning, Brass/Fire, Bronze/Lightning, Copper/Acid, Gold/Fire, Green/Poison, Red/Fire, Silver/Cold, White/Cold). You speak Draconic. Whenever you make a Charisma check for interaction with dragons, double proficiency."},{"level":1,"name":"Draconic Resilience","desc":"Maximum HP increases by 1 per sorcerer level. When not in armor, AC = 13 + Dexterity modifier."},{"level":6,"name":"Elemental Affinity","desc":"When you cast a spell that deals damage of your dragon ancestor type, add Charisma modifier to one damage roll. Spend 1 sorcery point to gain resistance to that damage type for 1 hour."},{"level":14,"name":"Dragon Wings","desc":"As a bonus action, sprout dragon wings (if not wearing armor). Fly speed = walk speed. Permanent."},{"level":18,"name":"Draconic Presence","desc":"As an action, emit an aura of awe or fear (60 ft) for 1 minute. Creatures must make Wisdom saves or be Charmed/Frightened (choose). Costs 5 sorcery points."}]},{"name":"Draconic Bloodline (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Draconic Resilience now scales more aggressively; Dragon Wings can be used with armor.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Draconic Resilience","desc":"HP maximum increases by 3 at level 3, then by 1 at each subsequent Sorcerer level. AC = 13 + Dexterity modifier when not wearing armor."},{"level":3,"name":"Elemental Affinity","desc":"When you cast a spell that deals damage of your Dragon Ancestor type, add your Charisma modifier to one roll of that spell's damage. You can also spend 1 Sorcery Point to gain Resistance to that damage type for 1 hour."},{"level":6,"name":"Dragon Wings","desc":"As a Bonus Action, cause spectral dragon wings to sprout from your back. Fly Speed = walk Speed. Lasts until you dismiss (Bonus Action) or become Incapacitated. No armor restriction."},{"level":14,"name":"Dragon Companion","desc":"You can cast Summon Dragon (from Fizban's Treasury of Dragons) without a spell slot once per Long Rest. While the dragon is summoned, you can use a Bonus Action to command it (instead of an Action)."},{"level":18,"name":"Draconic Presence","desc":"Spend 5 Sorcery Points (action) to emit an aura of awe or fear in 60 feet for 1 minute. Creatures must make Wisdom saves or be Charmed or Frightened for the duration."}]},{"name":"Wild Magic (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Wild Magic sorcerers draw power from the chaos of raw magical energy that suffuses their being.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Wild Magic Surge","desc":"When you cast a sorcerer spell of 1st level or higher, the DM can call for you to roll d20. On a 1, roll on Wild Magic Surge table (100 entries)."},{"level":1,"name":"Tides of Chaos","desc":"Gain advantage on one attack roll, ability check, or saving throw. Once used, the DM can (at will) trigger a Wild Magic Surge when you cast a spell before you can use Tides of Chaos again."},{"level":6,"name":"Bend Luck","desc":"When another creature you can see makes an attack roll, ability check, or save, spend 2 sorcery points: add or subtract 1d4 from the roll (reaction)."},{"level":14,"name":"Controlled Chaos","desc":"When you roll on the Wild Magic Surge table, roll twice and use either result."},{"level":18,"name":"Spell Bombardment","desc":"When you roll damage for a spell and roll the highest number on any dice, roll that die again and add to total. Per spell cast."}]},{"name":"Wild Magic (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Wild Magic Surge now triggers more consistently; Tides of Chaos reworked.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Wild Magic Surge","desc":"Whenever you cast a Sorcerer spell of level 1 or higher, roll d20. On a 20, roll on the Wild Magic Surge table."},{"level":3,"name":"Tides of Chaos","desc":"Once per Long Rest, gain Advantage on one D20 Test. On any subsequent Sorcerer spell you cast before your next Long Rest, a Wild Magic Surge automatically occurs."},{"level":6,"name":"Bend Luck","desc":"As a Reaction, spend 2 Sorcery Points to roll 1d4 and add or subtract it from another creature's attack roll, ability check, or saving throw."},{"level":14,"name":"Controlled Chaos","desc":"When you roll on the Wild Magic Surge table, roll twice and choose which result to use."},{"level":18,"name":"Spell Bombardment","desc":"Once per turn, when you roll damage for a spell and roll the highest possible number on any die, you can roll that die again and add the result."}]},{"name":"Storm Sorcery","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything / Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Storm Sorcerers have a natural bond with stormy weather and lightning, unlocked through their bloodline or birth in stormy conditions.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Wind Speaker","desc":"Speak, read, and write Primordial (includes Aquan, Auran, Ignan, Terran)."},{"level":1,"name":"Tempestuous Magic","desc":"Before or after casting a spell of 1st level or higher, fly up to 10 feet without provoking OAs."},{"level":6,"name":"Heart of the Storm","desc":"Resistance to lightning and thunder damage. When you cast a spell that deals lightning or thunder damage, creatures within 10 feet take lightning or thunder damage = half your sorcerer level."},{"level":6,"name":"Storm Guide","desc":"Stop rain in 20-ft radius as action (concentration). Redirect wind in 100-ft radius (concentration, bonus action each turn)."},{"level":14,"name":"Storm's Fury","desc":"When hit in melee, deal 2d6 lightning to the attacker (Str save or pushed 20 ft). Reaction."},{"level":18,"name":"Wind Soul","desc":"Immunity to lightning and thunder. Fly speed 60 ft. As action, grant allies within 30 ft fly speed 30 ft for 1 hour. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Divine Soul","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Divine Soul sorcerers carry a divine spark, granting them access to cleric spells alongside their sorcery.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Divine Magic","desc":"Access the entire Cleric spell list (in addition to Sorcerer). Choose one additional spell from Cleric list. Your spellcasting affinity color reflects your divine origin (Good = radiant, Evil = necrotic, Lawful = abjuration, Chaotic = transmutation, Neutral = either)."},{"level":1,"name":"Favored by the Gods","desc":"When you fail a death save or miss an attack roll, add 2d4 to the result. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Empowered Healing","desc":"Once per turn, when you or an ally within 5 feet rolls dice to restore HP with a spell, reroll any dice (spend 1 sorcery point). Must use new roll."},{"level":14,"name":"Otherworldly Wings","desc":"Use bonus action to manifest wings: angelic (fly speed 30, immune to difficult terrain), bat (fly speed 30, Darkvision 60 ft). Permanent."},{"level":18,"name":"Unearthly Recovery","desc":"When below half HP, use bonus action to regain HP equal to half HP max. Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"Shadow Magic","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Shadow Magic sorcerers draw power from the Shadowfell, wielding darkness and death magic.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Eyes of the Dark","desc":"Darkvision 120 ft. At 3rd level: cast Darkness for 1 sorcery point; you can see through magical Darkness from this spell."},{"level":1,"name":"Strength of the Grave","desc":"When damage reduces you to 0 HP, make a Charisma save (DC = 5 + damage dealt). On success, drop to 1 HP instead. Doesn't trigger from radiant or critical hits. Once per long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Hound of Ill Omen","desc":"Spend 3 sorcery points: summon a Hound of Ill Omen (a dire wolf with 50 HP and HP halved from other effects, speeds boosted). It tracks one target; target can't benefit from resistance to the hound's damage. Lasts 5 minutes."},{"level":14,"name":"Shadow Walk","desc":"When in dim light or darkness, use bonus action to teleport up to 120 feet to an unoccupied spot also in dim/dark."},{"level":18,"name":"Umbral Form","desc":"Spend 6 sorcery points: transform for 1 minute. Resistance to all damage except force and radiant; move through objects and creatures (can't end inside); Darkvision doesn't reveal you."}]},{"name":"Aberrant Mind","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Aberrant Mind sorcerers carry a link to the alien intellect of Far Realm entities, wielding psionic power.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Psionic Spells","desc":"Arms of Hadar, Calm Emotions, Detect Thoughts, Dissonant Whispers, and Mind Sliver are always prepared. These can be cast using Sorcery Points instead of spell slots (1 sorcery point per spell level)."},{"level":1,"name":"Telepathic Speech","desc":"As a bonus action, create a telepathic link with a willing creature within 30 feet for Charisma modifier minutes (min 1). Can communicate silently."},{"level":6,"name":"Psionic Sorcery","desc":"When casting a psionic spell, you can spend Sorcery Points instead of a spell slot (1 per spell level). If cast this way, the spell requires no verbal or somatic components."},{"level":6,"name":"Psychic Defenses","desc":"Resistance to Psychic damage. Advantage on saves vs. Charmed and Frightened."},{"level":14,"name":"Revelation in Flesh","desc":"Spend 1+ Sorcery Points as bonus action. 10 minutes each: 1 SP = swim speed = walk, breathe water. 2 SP = see in darkness. 3 SP = move through objects (can't end inside). 4 SP = fly speed = walk."},{"level":18,"name":"Warping Implosion","desc":"As action, teleport up to 120 feet. Each creature within 30 feet of departure point makes Str save or takes 3d10 force damage and is pulled 30 feet toward where you departed. Once per long rest (or 5 Sorcery Points)."}]},{"name":"Clockwork Soul","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Clockwork Soul sorcerers draw from the plane of Mechanus, wielding the power of cosmic order to nullify chaos.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Clockwork Magic","desc":"Always-prepared spells at each level: Alarm, Protection from Evil and Good, Aid, Lesser Restoration, Dispel Magic, Protection from Energy, Freedom of Movement, Summon Construct, Wall of Force, Hold Monster. Can replace one with any Wizard or Cleric spell once per long rest (as ritual)."},{"level":1,"name":"Restore Balance","desc":"When a creature is about to roll with advantage or disadvantage, use your reaction to cancel either. Proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Bastion of Law","desc":"Spend 1–5 Sorcery Points as action. Target creature (including self) within 30 feet gains a ward: 1d8 temporary HP per SP spent. When the target takes damage, the ward's temp HP is depleted first; the remainder reduces damage."},{"level":14,"name":"Trance of Order","desc":"As bonus action, enter a state of focus for 1 minute: treat rolls below 10 on d20 as 10; enemies can't have advantage on attacks vs. you. Once per long rest (or 5 Sorcery Points)."},{"level":18,"name":"Clockwork Cavalcade","desc":"Summon spirits of order in a 30-ft cube. They restore 4d8+8 HP to each creature in the area; repair all damaged objects; dispel all spells of 6th level and lower. Once per long rest (or 7 Sorcery Points)."}]}],"Warlock":[{"name":"The Archfey (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Archfey patrons are powerful fey lords and ladies whose pacts grant glamour and enchantment powers.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Fey Presence","desc":"As action, project beguiling/dreadful presence in a 10-ft cube. Creatures in the area make a Wisdom save or be Charmed or Frightened (your choice) until end of your next turn. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Misty Escape","desc":"When you take damage, use reaction to turn invisible and teleport up to 60 feet. Remains until start of next turn or until you attack/cast. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Beguiling Defenses","desc":"Immunity to Charmed condition. When a creature tries to charm you, it must make a Wisdom save (DC = spell save DC) or be Charmed by you for 1 minute."},{"level":14,"name":"Dark Delirium","desc":"As action, send a creature you can see within 60 feet into a dream-like state. Wisdom save (DC = spell save DC) or be Charmed or Frightened (your choice) for 1 minute, and their mind is flooded with illusions. Once per short/long rest."}]},{"name":"The Archfey (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024 Archfey. Now called 'Archfey Patron'. Steps of the Fey replaces Misty Escape.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Archfey Spells","desc":"Always prepared: Calm Emotions, Faerie Fire, Misty Step, Phantasmal Force, Sleep, Blink, Plant Growth, Dominate Beast, Greater Invisibility, Seeming."},{"level":3,"name":"Steps of the Fey","desc":"You can cast Misty Step without expending a spell slot a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum 1). Regain uses on Long Rest. In addition, when you cast Misty Step, you can give the destination space an effect: Refreshing Step (you or one visible creature within 10 ft regains 1d10 HP) or Taunting Step (the space is Difficult Terrain for enemies until your next Long Rest)."},{"level":6,"name":"Misty Escape","desc":"When you take damage, use Reaction to cast Misty Step (even if you already used all your Steps of the Fey uses). Also, you become Invisible until start of your next turn after teleporting. Once per Short or Long Rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Beguiling Defenses","desc":"Immunity to Charmed condition. When a creature attempts to Charm you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be Charmed by you for 1 minute."},{"level":14,"name":"Bewitching Magic","desc":"When you cast a Warlock spell using a spell slot, you can simultaneously cast Charm Person or Hold Person without expending a spell slot (using the spell's normal DC). Once per Long Rest."}]},{"name":"The Fiend (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Fiend patrons are powerful demons or devils who offer power in exchange for souls or service.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Dark One's Blessing","desc":"When you reduce a hostile creature to 0 HP, gain temp HP = Charisma modifier + Warlock level."},{"level":6,"name":"Dark One's Own Luck","desc":"When you make an ability check or saving throw, add 1d10 to the result. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Fiendish Resilience","desc":"After a short or long rest, choose one damage type. You have resistance to that type until you choose another."},{"level":14,"name":"Hurl Through Hell","desc":"When you hit with an attack, send the target through Hell briefly. It takes 10d10 psychic damage at end of your turn (Con save for half). Once per long rest."}]},{"name":"The Fiend (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Fiend Patron now includes Fiend Spells and Hurl Through Hell is more reliable.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Fiend Spells","desc":"Always prepared: Burning Hands, Command, Blindness/Deafness, Scorching Ray, Fireball, Stinking Cloud, Fire Shield, Wall of Fire, Flame Strike, Hallow."},{"level":3,"name":"Dark One's Blessing","desc":"When you reduce a creature to 0 HP, gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Charisma modifier + Warlock level (minimum 1)."},{"level":6,"name":"Dark One's Own Luck","desc":"When you make a D20 Test, add 1d10 to your roll. Once per Short or Long Rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Fiendish Resilience","desc":"Choose one damage type when you finish a Short or Long Rest. You gain Resistance to that type until you choose a different one."},{"level":14,"name":"Hurl Through Hell","desc":"When you hit a creature with an attack roll, send the target on a journey through the lower planes. At end of your turn, the target takes 8d10 Psychic damage. Once per Long Rest."}]},{"name":"The Great Old One (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Great Old One patrons are unfathomable entities from beyond reality—Cthulhu-like beings of cosmic power.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Awakened Mind","desc":"Telepathically speak with any creature you can see within 30 feet. No need for a shared language. They can respond only if they have a language."},{"level":6,"name":"Entropic Ward","desc":"When attacked, impose disadvantage on the attack roll (reaction). If it misses, gain advantage on your next attack vs. the attacker this turn. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Thought Shield","desc":"Your thoughts can't be read by telepathy or magic. Resistance to Psychic damage. When a creature deals psychic damage to you, it takes the same amount."},{"level":14,"name":"Create Thrall","desc":"Touch an Incapacitated humanoid to charm it. While charmed, it obeys commands, you have telepathic link within 1 mile, and it can't be charmed by others. Lasts until a Remove Curse is cast."}]},{"name":"The Great Old One (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Awakened Mind upgraded; Psychic Spells always prepared.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Great Old One Spells","desc":"Always prepared: Detect Thoughts, Dissonant Whispers, Phantasmal Force, Sending, Telekinesis, Clairvoyance, Hunger of Hadar, Dominate Monster, Feeblemind, Weird."},{"level":3,"name":"Awakened Mind","desc":"Telepathically communicate with any creature you can see within 30 feet. They can respond if they know at least one language. Additionally, if you cast a spell that targets a creature, you can use a Bonus Action to deal 2d6 Psychic damage to the target (once per spell cast)."},{"level":6,"name":"Clairvoyant Combatant","desc":"When you strike a creature with an attack roll, you can open a limited telepathic link. Until start of your next turn, it can't benefit from any AC bonuses (from features, spells, or magic) while within 30 feet of you. Once per Short or Long Rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Thought Shield","desc":"Your thoughts can't be read by telepathy. You gain Resistance to Psychic damage. When a creature deals Psychic damage to you, it takes the same amount."},{"level":14,"name":"Create Thrall","desc":"Touch an Incapacitated creature to charm it indefinitely. While charmed: obeys commands, you have a telepathic link within 1 mile, it can't be charmed by others. Broken by Remove Curse."}]},{"name":"The Hexblade","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Hexblade warlocks forge a pact with a mysterious entity from the Shadowfell that manifests through sentient magic weapons.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Hexblade's Curse","desc":"As bonus action, curse a creature within 30 feet for 1 minute. Gain bonus to damage rolls = proficiency bonus; score critical hits on 19-20; regain HP = prof bonus + Charisma modifier if cursed creature dies. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":1,"name":"Hex Warrior","desc":"Proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons. Choose one weapon to use Charisma instead of Str/Dex (refreshes on long rest; also includes Pact of the Blade weapons automatically)."},{"level":6,"name":"Accursed Specter","desc":"When you kill a humanoid, you can curse the soul. It rises as a specter (your control) for 24 hours, until dawn, or until destroyed. Once per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Armor of Hexes","desc":"If your cursed target hits you with an attack, roll d6: on 4+, the attack misses automatically."},{"level":14,"name":"Master of Hexes","desc":"When a creature under Hexblade's Curse dies, you can immediately curse a new creature within 30 feet (no action needed). Lose all temp HP from original curse."}]},{"name":"The Celestial","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything","desc":"Celestial warlocks draw power from the Upper Planes—the realm of angels and sacred light—becoming agents of divine healing and radiance.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Expanded Spell List","desc":"Cure Wounds, Guiding Bolt (1st); Flaming Sphere, Lesser Restoration (2nd); Daylight, Revivify (3rd); Guardian of Faith, Wall of Fire (4th); Flame Strike, Greater Restoration (5th)."},{"level":1,"name":"Bonus Cantrips","desc":"Learn Light and Sacred Flame cantrips."},{"level":1,"name":"Healing Light","desc":"Bonus action to heal a creature within 60 feet. Spend dice from a pool of d6s (pool = 1 + Warlock level). Up to proficiency bonus dice per use. Regain pool on long rest."},{"level":6,"name":"Radiant Soul","desc":"Resistance to Radiant damage. Once per turn, add Charisma modifier to Radiant or Fire damage from Warlock spells or cantrips."},{"level":10,"name":"Celestial Resilience","desc":"When you finish a short or long rest, you and up to 5 allies gain temp HP = Warlock level + Charisma modifier."},{"level":14,"name":"Searing Vengeance","desc":"When you or an ally within 60 feet makes a death save and succeeds, that creature can radiate blazing light: deal 2d8 + Charisma modifier radiant damage to creatures within 30 feet and blind them until end of next turn. Also stand up immediately with half max HP."}]},{"name":"The Fathomless","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Fathomless warlocks draw power from the dark ocean depths, commanding tentacles and aquatic forces.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Tentacle of the Deeps","desc":"Summon a 10-ft long spectral tentacle at a point within 60 feet (bonus action). Lasts 1 minute. Creatures that start their turn within 10 ft: Str save or take 1d8 Cold damage and speed reduced 10 ft. Melee attack from tentacle as bonus action. Tentacle moves with your bonus action. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":1,"name":"Gift of the Sea","desc":"Breathe underwater. Swim speed 40 ft."},{"level":6,"name":"Oceanic Soul","desc":"Resistance to Cold. While submerged, telepathically communicate with any creature within 30 feet that can breathe water."},{"level":6,"name":"Guardian Coil","desc":"When you or a creature within 10 feet of your tentacle takes damage, the tentacle can reduce damage by 1d8. Once per round."},{"level":10,"name":"Grasping Tentacles","desc":"Once per long rest (or 1st-level slot), cast Evard's Black Tentacles. While active, you gain temp HP = Warlock level and are immune to being restrained."},{"level":14,"name":"Fathomless Plunge","desc":"As action, teleport yourself and up to 5 willing creatures you can see within 30 ft to a location within 1 mile (must touch a large body of water at departure and arrival). Once per short/long rest."}]},{"name":"The Genie","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Genie warlocks form a pact with a noble genie—a dao (earth), djinni (air), efreeti (fire), or marid (water)—and channel their elemental power.","features":[{"level":1,"name":"Genie's Vessel","desc":"You have a magical vessel (bottle, lamp, ring). It is your spellcasting focus. You can enter the vessel (action) to rest inside (portable extradimensional space, 1 hour/Warlock level per short/long rest cycle). Vessel has AC = 10 + prof + Cha mod; HP = Warlock level + Cha mod; destroyed by damage or losing attunement."},{"level":1,"name":"Bottled Respite","desc":"Once per long rest, enter your Genie's Vessel as an action. Inside lasts up to Warlock level hours. Time passes at same rate; can hear 30 feet around vessel."},{"level":1,"name":"Genie's Wrath","desc":"Once per turn on a hit, deal extra damage: Dao (bludgeoning), Djinni (thunder), Efreeti (fire), Marid (cold). Damage = proficiency bonus."},{"level":6,"name":"Elemental Gift","desc":"Resistance to matching element: Dao (bludgeoning), Djinni (thunder), Efreeti (fire), Marid (cold). Fly or swim speed 30 ft (Djinni and Marid: fly; Dao and Marid: burrow/swim). Bonus action, proficiency bonus times per long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Sanctuary Vessel","desc":"When you enter the Genie's Vessel, up to 5 creatures within 30 ft can come with you. Inside: short rest = 10 minutes. Any creature inside can take a bonus action to heal 1d8 × proficiency bonus HP. Once per short rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Limited Wish","desc":"Once per 1d4 long rests, cast any spell of 6th level or lower from any class's list (no material components). The spell doesn't count against spells known or spell slots."}]}],"Wizard":[{"name":"School of Evocation (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Evocation wizards focus on spells that harness raw elemental energy, devastating enemies with fire and lightning.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Evocation Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Evocation spells into spellbook halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Sculpt Spells","desc":"When casting an Evocation spell that forces a save, choose up to 1 + spell level creatures to automatically succeed and take no damage (if normally half damage)."},{"level":6,"name":"Potent Cantrip","desc":"Your damaging cantrips deal half damage to targets that succeed on their saving throws."},{"level":10,"name":"Empowered Evocation","desc":"Add Intelligence modifier to damage roll of any Wizard evocation spell."},{"level":14,"name":"Overchannel","desc":"When casting a Wizard spell of 1st through 5th level that deals damage, deal maximum damage instead of rolling. First use: no side effect. Each use after: take 2d12 necrotic per spell level (no resistance/immunity applies)."}]},{"name":"School of Evocation (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Sculpt Spells is now available from level 3. Overchannel reworked.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Sculpt Spells","desc":"When you cast an Evocation spell that affects other creatures, choose up to 1 + spell level of those creatures to automatically succeed on any saving throws, taking no damage if they would normally take half."},{"level":3,"name":"Potent Cantrip","desc":"When a creature succeeds on a save against your damaging cantrip, the creature takes half the cantrip's damage."},{"level":6,"name":"Empowered Evocation","desc":"When you cast any Wizard evocation spell, add your Intelligence modifier to one damage roll of the spell."},{"level":10,"name":"Overchannel","desc":"When you cast a Wizard spell with a spell slot that deals damage, maximize all of the spell's damage dice. After using this feature, you can use it again on the next turn at the cost of taking 2d12 Necrotic per spell level (no resistance). Proficiency Bonus times per Long Rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Durable Magic","desc":"While concentrating on a spell, you gain +2 AC and all saving throws."}]},{"name":"School of Abjuration (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Abjurers specialize in defensive and protective magic, weaving wards that keep allies safe.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Abjuration Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Abjuration spells into spellbook halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Arcane Ward","desc":"When you cast an Abjuration spell of 1st level or higher, create a magical ward. It has HP = 2× Wizard level + Int modifier. Damage that reduces you to 0 hits the ward first. Casting another Abjuration of 1st+ replenishes 2× spell level HP (can't exceed max)."},{"level":6,"name":"Projected Ward","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet takes damage, use your reaction to have the Arcane Ward absorb the damage instead."},{"level":10,"name":"Improved Abjuration","desc":"Add your proficiency bonus to ability checks made as part of casting Abjuration spells (e.g., Counterspell check)."},{"level":14,"name":"Spell Resistance","desc":"Advantage on saving throws against spells. Resistance to spell damage."}]},{"name":"School of Abjuration (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Arcane Ward scales better; Spell Resistance available at level 14.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Arcane Ward","desc":"When you cast an Abjuration spell of level 1 or higher, a ward forms around you. HP = twice your Wizard level + Intelligence modifier. Absorbs damage directed at you. Casting Abjuration spells replenishes 2× spell level HP (max remains the same)."},{"level":3,"name":"Abjuration Savant","desc":"Time and gold to copy Abjuration spells halved."},{"level":6,"name":"Projected Ward","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet takes damage, use your Reaction to transfer it to your Arcane Ward instead."},{"level":10,"name":"Improved Abjuration","desc":"Add Proficiency Bonus to any ability check made as part of an Abjuration spell."},{"level":14,"name":"Spell Resistance","desc":"Advantage on saving throws against spells. Resistance to damage from spells."}]},{"name":"School of Conjuration","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Conjurers focus on summoning creatures and objects from elsewhere in the multiverse.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Conjuration Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Conjuration spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Minor Conjuration","desc":"As an action, conjure a nonmagical object (up to 3 ft × 3 ft, 10 lbs) in an unoccupied space within 10 feet. Lasts 1 hour, vanishes when you die or use Minor Conjuration again."},{"level":6,"name":"Benign Transposition","desc":"Teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. Or swap places with a willing Small or Medium creature within 30 feet. Once per long rest (or Conjuration spell slot used)."},{"level":10,"name":"Focused Conjuration","desc":"Concentration on a Conjuration spell can't be broken by taking damage."},{"level":14,"name":"Durable Summons","desc":"Any creature summoned or created by your Conjuration spell has 30 extra HP."}]},{"name":"School of Divination","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Diviners uncover secrets of the future, enabling them to manipulate outcomes with portentous foresight.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Divination Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Divination spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Portent","desc":"After a long rest, roll 2 d20s (3 at level 14). Record the results. Once per roll, replace any d20 roll with one of these results (before or after the roll but before outcome is known)."},{"level":6,"name":"Expert Divination","desc":"When you cast a Divination spell of 2nd level or higher using a spell slot, regain one expended spell slot of a lower level (max 5th)."},{"level":10,"name":"The Third Eye","desc":"Bonus action, once per short/long rest: choose Darkvision 60 ft, see through magical darkness 60 ft, see invisible creatures 10 ft, or read any language."},{"level":14,"name":"Greater Portent","desc":"Roll 3 d20s for Portent instead of 2."}]},{"name":"School of Enchantment","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Enchanters specialize in affecting the minds of others, compelling, confusing, or beguiling creatures.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Enchantment Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Enchantment spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Hypnotic Gaze","desc":"As action, choose one creature within 5 feet: Int save or Charmed and Incapacitated until end of next turn. Usable again each turn (same creature) without recasting. If creature saves: can't target it again for 24 hours. Once per long rest between targets."},{"level":6,"name":"Instinctive Charm","desc":"When a creature within 30 feet makes an attack roll against you, use reaction: creature must make Wisdom save or redirect its attack to the nearest creature other than you. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":10,"name":"Split Enchantment","desc":"When you cast an Enchantment spell that targets only one creature, target a second creature with it."},{"level":14,"name":"Alter Memories","desc":"When you cast an Enchantment spell that Charms, the target doesn't remember being Charmed by you. Additionally, you can make the target forget up to 1 hour per Wizard level of memories (ending the charm)."}]},{"name":"School of Illusion","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Illusionists master the art of deceiving the senses and fooling the mind with powerful false images.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Illusion Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Illusion spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Improved Minor Illusion","desc":"Learn Minor Illusion (or choose another cantrip if already known). Can include both a sound and an image with a single casting."},{"level":6,"name":"Malleable Illusions","desc":"When you cast an Illusion spell with a duration of 1 minute or more, use your action to change the nature of that illusion (using whatever parameters the spell allows)."},{"level":10,"name":"Illusory Self","desc":"When a creature hits you with an attack, interpose an illusory duplicate: the attack misses. Once per short/long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Illusory Reality","desc":"When you cast an Illusion spell of 1st level or higher, make one nonmagical object in the illusion real. Lasts 1 minute; can't deal damage or directly harm."}]},{"name":"School of Necromancy (2014)","source":"Player's Handbook 2014","desc":"Necromancers study the forces that animate life and death, raising armies of the undead.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Necromancy Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Necromancy spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Grim Harvest","desc":"When you kill a creature with a spell of 1st level or higher, regain HP = 2× spell level (3× for Necromancy spells). Doesn't work on constructs or undead."},{"level":6,"name":"Undead Thralls","desc":"Add Animate Dead to spellbook if not present. When casting Animate Dead: animate one extra undead; undead gain max HP bonus = Wizard level; undead add proficiency bonus to damage."},{"level":10,"name":"Inured to Undeath","desc":"Resistance to necrotic damage. Max HP can't be reduced."},{"level":14,"name":"Command Undead","desc":"As action, make one undead within 60 feet make a Charisma saving throw. On fail: falls under your control for 24 hours (re-save at end of each 24-hour period). Undead with Int ≥ 8 have advantage on the save."}]},{"name":"School of Necromancy (2024)","source":"Player's Handbook 2024","desc":"Updated 2024. Undead Thralls improved; Command Undead available at level 14.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Grim Harvest","desc":"When you kill a creature with a spell of level 1 or higher, regain HP equal to twice the spell's level (3× for Necromancy spells). Doesn't work on Constructs or Undead."},{"level":3,"name":"Necromancy Savant","desc":"Time and gold to copy Necromancy spells halved."},{"level":6,"name":"Undead Thralls","desc":"Animate Dead always prepared. When you cast Animate Dead, animate one additional corpse. Undead you animate gain bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls = your Proficiency Bonus, and hit point maximum = Wizard level."},{"level":10,"name":"Inured to Undeath","desc":"Resistance to Necrotic damage. Your hit point maximum can't be reduced."},{"level":14,"name":"Command Undead","desc":"As an Action, target one Undead within 60 feet: Charisma save (DC = spell save DC). Fail: the undead obeys your commands for 24 hours (repeat save at end of each 24 hours). Undead with Intelligence ≥ 8 have Advantage on the save."}]},{"name":"School of Transmutation","source":"Player's Handbook 2014 / 2024","desc":"Transmuters alter the physical world, transforming matter and energy at will.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Transmutation Savant","desc":"Gold and time to copy Transmutation spells halved."},{"level":2,"name":"Minor Alchemy","desc":"Transform one nonmagical object made entirely of one substance (wood, stone, iron, copper, silver) into another. Size: up to 1 cubic foot per 10 minutes of work. Reverts after an hour of not concentrating."},{"level":6,"name":"Transmuter's Stone","desc":"Create a stone (8 hours). While held, bearer gains one of: darkvision 60 ft, 10 ft speed increase, proficiency in Constitution saves, or resistance to acid/cold/fire/lightning/thunder (choose when making stone). Change the benefit when casting a Transmutation spell."},{"level":10,"name":"Shapechanger","desc":"Add Polymorph to spellbook if not present. Cast it on yourself without a spell slot (can't transform into creature requiring transformation components). Once per short/long rest."},{"level":14,"name":"Master Transmuter","desc":"As action, consume the Transmuter's Stone (destroys it) to: a) transmute one object into another (like creation spell), b) remove curses/diseases/poisons/attunements, c) end aging effects, or d) resurrect a dead creature within 1 round with full HP restoration."}]},{"name":"Bladesinging","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide","desc":"Bladesingers are elven (or elven-trained) warrior-wizards who weave fighting techniques with spellcasting in a deadly dance.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Training in War and Song","desc":"Proficiency with light armor, one one-handed melee weapon of choice. Proficiency in Performance."},{"level":2,"name":"Bladesong","desc":"Bonus action, twice per short/long rest. For 1 minute: add Intelligence modifier to AC; walk speed +10 ft; advantage on Acrobatics; add Intelligence modifier to Concentration saves. Ends if unconscious, heavy armor/shield worn, two-handed weapon, or use it again."},{"level":6,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"Attack twice per Attack action. One of these attacks can be replaced with a cantrip."},{"level":10,"name":"Song of Defense","desc":"While Bladesong is active and you take damage, use reaction to expend a spell slot: reduce damage by 5× the slot level."},{"level":14,"name":"Song of Victory","desc":"While Bladesong active, add Intelligence modifier to melee weapon attack damage rolls."}]},{"name":"Order of Scribes","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Scribes wizards are bookworms who bring their spellbook to life as a familiar and can adapt their magic on the fly.","features":[{"level":2,"name":"Awakened Spellbook","desc":"Animate your spellbook as a familiar-like companion. It can use a bonus action to fly up to 30 ft. You can use it as a focus for Wizard spells. When casting a ritual with the book, the ritual takes only the normal cast time. Use it to swap out damage types of spells you know."},{"level":2,"name":"Master Scrivener","desc":"In 2 hours and for 10 gp, create a scroll of a spell in your spellbook (up to 2nd level). Scroll is usable by anyone attuned to it. Scroll crumbles after use."},{"level":6,"name":"One with the Word","desc":"Your mind syncs with the spellbook. Advantage on Intelligence saves. If damaged while concentrating on a spell, use reaction: retain concentration, but erase one spell (your choice) from spellbook (can be rewritten later)."},{"level":10,"name":"Manifest Mind","desc":"As bonus action, manifest your spellbook's consciousness as a spectral presence anywhere within 300 feet. You can cast spells as if you were in its space. Lasts until dismissed or 10 minutes."},{"level":14,"name":"Master Scrivener (Upgrade)","desc":"Create scrolls of 3rd-level spells as well. The bonus actions and bonuses from Manifest Mind increase as you level."}]}],"Artificer":[{"name":"Alchemist","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Eberron: Forge of the Artificer","desc":"Alchemists experiment with potions and elixirs to support allies and disable enemies.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Tool Proficiency","desc":"Gain proficiency with Alchemist's Supplies."},{"level":3,"name":"Alchemist Spells","desc":"Healing Word, Ray of Sickness; Flaming Sphere, Melf's Acid Arrow; Gaseous Form, Mass Healing Word; Blight, Death Ward; Cloudkill, Raise Dead."},{"level":3,"name":"Experimental Elixir","desc":"After each long rest, produce a number of elixirs equal to your proficiency bonus (minimum 2). Roll or choose each elixir's effect: Healing (2d4+int mod HP), Swiftness (+10 speed), Resilience (+1 AC), Boldness (advantage on saves vs. frightened and charmed), Flight (10 min fly speed 10 ft), Transformation (Alter Self 10 min). Can spend spell slots to make more."},{"level":5,"name":"Alchemical Savant","desc":"Spells that restore HP or deal acid, fire, necrotic, or poison damage add Intelligence modifier to one roll."},{"level":9,"name":"Restorative Reagents","desc":"Experimental Elixirs also grant temp HP = 2d6+Int mod. Cast Lesser Restoration without spell slot (Int mod times per long rest)."},{"level":15,"name":"Chemical Mastery","desc":"Immunity to poison and disease. Cast Greater Restoration and Heal each once per long rest (no spell slot)."}]},{"name":"Armorer","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Armorers modify magical armor to become a weapon and shield, transforming themselves into walking fortresses.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Tools of the Trade","desc":"Proficiency with heavy armor and Smith's Tools."},{"level":3,"name":"Arcane Armor","desc":"Over 1 hour (long rest), turn a suit of heavy armor into Arcane Armor. It can't be removed without your consent; replaces any missing limbs; counts as a spellcasting focus."},{"level":3,"name":"Armor Model","desc":"Choose Guardian (melee focused: gauntlet attacks 1d8 thunder, enemies hit are slowed) or Infiltrator (ranged: built-in lightning launcher 1d6 lightning, become harder to perceive in dim light). Can switch on long rest."},{"level":5,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"Attack twice per Attack action."},{"level":9,"name":"Armor Modifications","desc":"Infuse separate parts of Arcane Armor (helmet, chestplate, gauntlets, boots) with separate infusions (up to 4 parts)."},{"level":15,"name":"Perfected Armor","desc":"Guardian: knockback on hit, pull creatures 30 ft within 60 ft (once per turn). Infiltrator: attacks against a creature marked by lightning launcher have advantage."}]},{"name":"Artillerist","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything","desc":"Artillerists specialize in using magical turrets and wands to blast enemies from a distance.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Tool Proficiency","desc":"Gain proficiency with Woodcarver's Tools."},{"level":3,"name":"Artillerist Spells","desc":"Shield, Thunderwave; Scorching Ray, Shatter; Fireball, Wind Wall; Ice Storm, Wall of Fire; Cone of Cold, Wall of Force."},{"level":3,"name":"Eldritch Cannon","desc":"Create a magical artillery piece (Flamethrower, Force Ballista, or Protector). It acts on your initiative (bonus action to command). Small or Tiny size. 60/120 HP. Lasts 1 hour. Once per long rest (extra per spell slot)."},{"level":5,"name":"Arcane Firearm","desc":"Create a wand, staff, or rod. When using it as a focus for Artificer spells, one damage die of the spell is enhanced (+1d8)."},{"level":9,"name":"Explosive Cannon","desc":"Eldritch Cannon +1d8 damage. Can destroy it as action (60 ft, Dex save, 3d8 force)."},{"level":15,"name":"Fortified Position","desc":"Create two Eldritch Cannons per long rest. Half cover for you and allies within 10 feet of a cannon."}]},{"name":"Battle Smith","source":"Tasha's Cauldron of Everything / Eberron: Forge of the Artificer","desc":"Battle Smiths bond with a mechanical companion—a Steel Defender—and fight with magical weapons.","features":[{"level":3,"name":"Tool Proficiency","desc":"Proficiency with Smith's Tools."},{"level":3,"name":"Battle Smith Spells","desc":"Heroism, Shield; Branding Smite, Warding Bond; Aura of Vitality, Conjure Barrage; Aura of Purity, Fire Shield; Banishing Smite, Mass Cure Wounds."},{"level":3,"name":"Battle Ready","desc":"Proficiency with martial weapons. When using a weapon (magic), use Intelligence modifier for attacks and damage instead of Strength or Dexterity."},{"level":3,"name":"Steel Defender","desc":"Create a mechanical beast companion (stat block provided). It acts on its own initiative; uses your proficiency bonus. Takes Dodge action unless commanded otherwise (bonus action). Revive with Mending or spell slot."},{"level":5,"name":"Extra Attack","desc":"Attack twice per Attack action."},{"level":9,"name":"Arcane Jolt","desc":"When you or Steel Defender hits with a magic weapon attack: add 2d6 damage (force) to target, OR restore 2d6 HP to a creature within 30 ft of target. Intelligence modifier times per long rest."},{"level":15,"name":"Improved Defender","desc":"Steel Defender's Deflect Attack now reduces damage by 1d4 + proficiency bonus + Int mod. Arcane Jolt increases to 4d6."}]}]};
